"0#thank you|thanks for always being a sounding board, always being happy to jump into a meeting- a call- or a brainstorm. This is a consistent quality throughout the year but especially as of late- you make it easy to partner together and it is appreciated!\n\n1#meaningful mentoring|Amy thank you for being my mentor. It is amazing having the opportunity to share and learn from you. Thank you for giving up your time to this. The coolest thing is,  your words follow me around long after our conversation ends .\n\n2#Team Development, thank you!|Amy and MJ- this note is long overdue, but I wanted to take a moment to thank you both for the DiSC sessions.  Amy, thank you for arranging these sessions for the team‚Äî these sorts of things are so impactful for everyone‚Äôs development and have opened a lot of interesting conversations on my team.  MJ, a huge thank you to you for leading not one, but two engaging sessions‚Äîone for the team and one for the leadership group I attended separately. Your ability to spark meaningful conversations, and make it all so relatable is a gift.  I think I‚Äôve officially become ‚Äúthat person‚Äù who can‚Äôt stop talking about my High C.......  Thank you both for making these sessions so impactful and for all the work you do to help us grow as individuals and as a team.\n\n3#CCMA Awards...It certainly took a village :)|In Q4 2022, we embarked on a journey to transform our Quality Program though procuring and implementing CallMiner's conversation analytics tool within CS.   This took an enormous amount of effort from a dedicated bunch of humans who not only accepted the challenge but stepped up to learn new coding skills, beta tested with super users, changed how they did their day job, gave up their time to learn how to perform Quality Audits, automated Quality Audits, organized a successful on-site event, hours of copy writing and most importantly resulted in a phenomenal improvement to CS Quality that cements our premium service offering for our customers.  To me, it is no surprise to me that CCMA commended Workhuman for ‚ÄúThe Best Use of Technology ‚Äì Tactical Project‚Äù at the 2024 CCMA Awards and I can‚Äôt thank this group enough for all the great work you did to make this happen. You should be extremely proud of your contribution, and I am grateful to work with such dedicated professionals. Thank you!\n\n4#Making Women & Allies Mentorship Pilot a Success!|Thank you all for participating in our first ever Women & Allies mentorship pilot program! Getting a mentorship program up and running has been a long-terms goal for W&A and your active participation, dedication, and enthusiasm have made it not only a reality, but a resounding success. Moreover, your feedback has been incredibly valuable as we plan for future cycles and refine the program further. Thank you again for sharing your knowledge and expertise as well as your openness to learning and being a part of a brand new initiative!\n\n5#Analysts Uncovered|Thank you both for taking the time to deliver such a well prepared, informational, presentation on analysts and our relationship with them as a company. They will be an important part of 2025 so everyone having a good understanding is essential.\n\n6#Zoom background moves fast, Amy moves faster|Thank you so much Amy for taking the time to jump on a call and talk about messaging for our upcoming ROI webinar. It was such a helpful step in working through the last-minute changes and webinar prep. And on a larger scale, I personally came away with even more clarity on how to continue evolving, improving, meeting new needs and approaching projects with purpose.  Thanks for always being willing to jump in, and for turning a touch-base meeting into a super valuable half hour. I know your Zoom background for 2025 will be just as inspirational\n\n7#Thanks for Making Me Feel Welcome in My First Week|I want to express my sincere gratitude to Amy, Jenna, Helen, Kamille, and Kayleigh. Everyone made my welcome to Workhuman a very warm one, and it made me feel right at home.   I look forward to working with everyone in the coming weeks on new projects and initiatives, to ensure all humans we work with are properly engaged and informed, so they can feel they're part of the initiatives in their own ways.\n\n8#Behind the Scenes Crew|Thank you to my behind the scenes crew for all of the support leading up to and during the Companywide Check-in. From multiple tech check sessions, to re-working the space and cameras so we could get the best lighting and views, to being live on slack throughout the meeting to work through the details live. It doesn't happen without a great team. I appreciate the partnership and the respect for quality! Thank you!\n\n9#What is a great week|OMG, what a great week!  I just have to say thank you for your enthusiasm during the AI Hackathon.  It was truly magical to discuss AI ideas with you, especially on how to increase recognition on the platform. It was amazing to see different areas coming together to work towards improving recognition.  Thanks again for all your effort‚Äîyou made my week so much fun!\n\n10#Plan the Work and Work the Plan|Team, thank you all for a highly collaborative, productive, and engaging workshop this week. We took two full days as a team to review program, cultural, and MELT performance. We were vulnerable and transparent, we questioned everything, we debated critical growth areas and areas of improvement. Tyler provided a HX strategy update on how we plan the org and foster unity in the marketing organization. We walked away with critical next steps that will inform the unified GTM strategy in 2025 while setting the stage for a great H2 and 2025. Thank you all for the participation, the preparation, and for driving the business forward.\n\n11#That's a Wrap|The 2024 Spotlight Series just wrapped up! The 2nd and 3rd episodes were only a month apart! Thank you for your participation. The work started almost a year ago and each of you said 'Yes' to your role, whether it was work that spanned over the year, or involved being recorded for a segment. A lot of work goes into this event - planning, sourcing, promo, web, tech support, scripting, recordings, post-production. The list is long, and so is the list of humans who support this event. The team learned and pivoted over the year, modified the segments, adjusted the promo, never gave up on sourcing speakers, got creative with recording locations, and masterfully edited the episodes to include the best of the best content. Spotlight is the bass guitar of the Events portfolio - the important steady beat supporting our message and a platform to share it with the world. Cheers to all of you!\n\n12#Clifton Strengths = Witchy Super Powers|Thank you for organizing the team-building session and arranging the CliftonStrengths tests for us. I find this kind of activity fascinating. Although it's no surprise that I get a bit uncomfortable with messiness, you were well-prepared to guide us in leveraging our individual strengths for personal, professional, and team growth and showed me how to communicate around the messy. We saw an immediate use case in how I relayed a project to a member of my team! And it worked! It was incredibly enjoyable to engage in this exercise with the Corp Comm Leaders, and it‚Äôs an experience I will continually revisit as I learn more about myself and advance in my career.  We make lots of jokes about witches in this group -- but I think you really gave us a way to consider and make use of our powers. Corps Comms witches forever <3\n\n13#Awesome Connect!|Alessandra, Anais and Amy - a thank you for the great meeting yesterday.   Alessandra, for your time, the pre-read work, and your openness to ideas and new ways of working.  Anais, all the efforts you have put into the analysis and the way you succinctly shared them with us.  Amy, for getting this band together!   I for one am pumped for what is to come and how we might be able to contribute to some big goals.   Thank you!\n\n14#Queens of team work - helping our IRE efforts|I wanted to take a moment to express to say a big THANK YOU for the collective effort of you all made to make the IRE government (Minister Peter Burke, IDA CEO, Michael Lohan and Enterprise Ireland CEO, Leo Clancy) visit to our Framingham office happen this week. It was a big lift - looking at you Allie and Becca and having to be at the office before 8:00 AM to give the tour,  all the behind-the-scenes strings to organize meetings with them while they are in the office, and the additional work before the visit itself. This is a huge help to our Dublin office in general, not only for PR but to help us achieve our business goals here and open doors in EMEA. Couldn't be more grateful to be working with such dedicated individuals! thank you thank you thank you!!!\n\n15#Survey says...|You win! Thank you for your speedy response to our process survey. Your input is valued!\n\n16#Grand Opening Helpers to the Rescue|THANK YOU!!!! I cannot express that enough that I appreciate each of you for taking time away from your days and helping us make this event run smoothly with the best experience! Thank you for your time and hope you enjoyed the day as we celebrated this big milestone!\n\n17#See something, DO something - Connecting the dots|Dave, I want to highlight and commend you for seeing an opportunity, taking quick action to bring the right people together in service to demonstrating to a client at risk another tentpole of the value of our partnership. Amy, thank you for acting with urgency and for fostering such excellent relationships with market leaders.  During a call with Maine Health (aka Maine Medical Center) Sue the VP of HR Shared Services name dropped Ed Boyle at Gallup that he was speaking at an upcoming HR team meeting. Hearing how Sue valued Ed's point of view, and also knowing Sue is currently leading a x-functional committee examining internal programs and their impact on employee engagement, and that they are considering making a pivot in their strategy around recognition, Dave, you quickly ghost-wrote an email that Amy could send to Ed asking for his support and endorsement of working with Workhuman. Amy, you jumped right on it, and within hours had this response:   \"You are so good at your job. How did you know about this meeting? I was literally made aware of it today. Of course I am up to a quick connect on this. Let me know what you need me to do and I will sort out how to work it into the session. Great to hear from you Amy.\"  That (visualize me pointing to the above) is the power of relationship, and a demonstration of how when all of us work together with a focused goal, we can move the needle, and do so quickly. Thank you Dave for connecting the dots between Gallup, Ed, Amy & Maine Health to seize an opportunity, and Thank you Amy for taking the baton passed to you and closing the loop.  I appreciate you both working quickly and confidently understanding who can help and taking the initiative to make it happen.\n\n18#In the midst of brilliance|As we reflect on the resounding success of WorkhumanLive Austin, I am compelled to extend my deepest gratitude and admiration to each of you. Your leadership has been instrumental in turning a bold vision into an awe-inspiring reality, cementing its status as the premier conference for business leaders worldwide.  Your meticulous attention to every facet of the event, from pre-promotion, central, design & experience to speakers, technology, production, communications and surrounding events, has transformed ambitious ideas into a seamless experience for over 3,000 attendees. Your ability to orchestrate, collaborate, and innovate‚Äîwhile setting egos aside‚Äîhas not only elevated our brand and the WHL \"product\" but has also reinforced our promise to the community we serve.  The dedication, creativity, and problem-solving skills you displayed were pivotal in crafting an event that not only met but surpassed expectations. The quality of the keynote speakers, the depth of the sessions, and the flawless overall execution ensured that every participant left feeling connected and inspired. Your efforts have strengthened our relationships with customers, partners, and prospects while enriching the HR community and paving the way for new opportunities in pipeline creation and customer retention. The spirit of collaboration and inclusivity you fostered has set a new benchmark for excellence and showcased the true essence of Workhuman.  I am truly grateful for your hard work, passion, and unwavering commitment to excellence. I'm so proud to have you on ALL on the team. Thank you, every one of you, for your significant contributions.   Richard\n\n19#True Wrangler|Amy, thank you for being the speaker handler for John Baldino at both the Newcomers on Tour and the Lone Star Social. Because of your expert wrangling, John was at each event on time and prepared with his talking points. These new events were being tested out this year and I think including John enhanced the experience for the attendees. Appreciate the support!\n\n20#Helping a guy out|Amy, thank you for thinking about the human (me) in addition to the audience on our first day of Live.  It was a long day, and I needed to complete all of the D1 reporting in the new template.  When I let you know I would not make it to your social event, you quickly sent me a picture of a small work room you had there, and encouraged me to join everyone there, have some food and drink, and continue to work.  It allowed me to be present, complete the days work, and also enjoy being around the team.  I appreciate you!\n\n21#We Did It! -- Workhuman Innovation Launch|Thanks to this groups' hard work, collaboration, and innovative mindset, we were able to successfully pull off Workhuman's first product innovation launch. This required a great deal of cross-functional collaboration and I deeply appreciate how all of these teams came together and supported one another to create a stunning web page, powerful marketing campaigns, and impactful enablement for our internal teams as well as our customers.  All of this effort goes a long way towards advancing Workhuman's innovation reputation and further separating us from the competition. Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!\n\n22#Taking Care of BOK Financial|Thank you all for supporting BOK Financial during Workhuman Live!   They had a FANTASTIC time at the event and felt truly taken care of. Each one of you supported their experience in a unique and important way. With an opportunity to move them over the line this year, they had multiple exclusive events like J Prime, Aba, meeting Brene Brown, and the Thursday Takeaway session. We have gotten extremely positive feedback throughout the event and post event. WHL won over key contacts at BOK Financial and we will be sure to use this momentum to accelerate the process.  Thank you!\n\n23#Thoughtful Leadership Makes a Team|Amy, I've been reflecting on last week at WHL, and three instances keep resonating with me that I want to express my gratitude for.  First, on Monday night at the Austin Taco Project, you were the only one who thought to offer me the chance to take a break from checking in speakers. It allowed me to mingle with them, which made such a difference in my interactions with them the rest of the week. Your inclusion made a significant difference, and I cherished that time.  Secondly, being included in Issa Rae's meet and greet backstage was unexpected and incredibly appreciated. As a newer member, I didn't anticipate to be included backstage at all. Your decision to invite me, even though you could have excluded me, was so thoughtful. It led to a memorable experience and a team moment in that photo opportunity with Issa that I would have missed otherwise.  Lastly, during Andy's book signing, you ensured I didn't miss a special moment when everyone headed to the room where Richard gave a \"cheers\" to our group. Your thoughtfulness in including me left a lasting impression.  So all of that to say, I just want to thank you, from the bottom of my heart, for your genuine thoughtfulness as a leader. I've always been in roles that often go overlooked by supervisors and members of leadership for some pretty cool opportunities like the three I mentioned here. And the fact that you were aware and thoughtful enough to include me, when you didn't have to, and when nobody else would have, is something I'll carry with me for the rest of my life. It truly means more than you'll ever know.  I feel incredibly fortunate to work for and alongside you. Thank you for everything you do.\n\n24#Workhuman Live Austin 2024!|As we revel in the success of WorkhumanLive Austin, I'm compelled to express my deepest gratitude and admiration for everyone who played a pivotal role in orchestrating what has indeed become the world's leading conference for business leaders. To our magnificent events team, your ability to transform our vision into a stunning reality is nothing short of miraculous. Every detail of the event was crafted with precision, turning ambitious ideas into an awe-inspiring experiences for over 3,000 attendees. Your dedication and creativity have not only set a new benchmark for excellence but have also showcased the true spirit of Workhuman. The cross-functional execution of the Sales, Marketing, and Customer teams was crucial in weaving the rich tapestry of this event. Your efforts have fortified our brand's promise and paved the way for new opportunities in pipeline creation and customer retention. I must also acknowledge our Workhuman back-office teams - your support over the last 18 months has been the backbone of our success from procurement and legal contracts to finance and administrative champions, your relentless support ensured that every piece fell perfectly into place.  Your collective attention to detail, problem-solving skills, and commitment to inclusivity have not only enhanced our relationships with customers, partners, prospects, and the entire HR community but also enriched the experience for every attendee. From the quality of the keynote speakers to the thought-provoking sessions and flawless execution, you all ensured that every participant left with a sense of connection and inspiration.  Thank you, each and every one of you, for your hard work, your passion, and your unwavering commitment to excellence. Here‚Äôs to your success and the continued growth of our event as a beacon for business leaders around the globe. Cheers to the entire team behind WorkhumanLive Austin!\n\n25#Writer‚Äôs Room|Thank you to the Workhuman Live Writer‚Äôs Room! I‚Äôve always wanted a writers room and you guys delivered. Having a sounding board, a place to discuss and brainstorm, to swap ideas, to tease out difficult narratives - this is what‚Äôs makes a story come alive. We always have to balance the heart and the head with this conference. It is a balance of altruism and direct business objectives. Getting that balance right can be infuriating at times and needs a thoughtful approach. I think we got the balance right. Jen, you were juggling so many strands and so many different voices, it is a wonder you didn‚Äôt go mad! Thank you all for your diligent efforts and creative energies. Well done!\n\n26#Avanade Case Study Filming Help|Thanks to you all for shortly disrupting your day to help capture b-roll for Avanade‚Äôs Microsoft Teams Case Study shoot.  Things came together last minute, but your willingness to support an initiative that will bring eyes and ears to this impactful integration is much appreciated.  Cheers!\n\n27#The most innovative leader|Amy,  Daily, I am floored by your unwavering dedication to driving innovation within our corp comms team.  Your encouragement of experimentation has encouraged us to push boundaries and explore uncharted ways and means of tackling projects.   Your strategic way of thinking, always with data in mind, coupled with your openness to new perspectives enables us to perform in new ways as a team together - you truly drive innovation and collaboration. Your ability to inspire and motivate others is setting a remarkable standard of leadership for us all. So lucky to be a part of your team.\n\n28#Department Meetings|Thank you all for the help, guidance, logistics and planning, that went into my department World Tour these past few weeks! It's actually a difficult thing to accomplish logistically. Getting the right amount of attendees, whilst making sure there was enough department concentration in each meeting so that I could tailor the talk to the specific circumstances, was a balancing act. I was disappointed that my rider at each location of Crunchies was cruelly ignored, but I pushed on ¬†üòÇ A special thank you to Amy who, mercilessly, had to sit through every one,  and listen to mostly the same talk track time after time - what an accomplishment! Seriously, thank you all for the endless help!\n\n29#We got this|What a few weeks for our tiny team of two. While the change we're going through could create anxiety, unease and fear in a person, I have none of these feelings. With you as my leader, I know we are making the right decisions and I believe whole heartedly that you are the greatest leader I have ever worked with. You care. About it all. Even the little things that no one should care about. Knowing I have you to support, guide and laugh with me through the week is what gets me up on a Monday morning. The Corp Comms team is hashtagblessed to have you.\n\n30#Many Thanks on this special occasion|Ladies, First off I am beyond blessed to work with such amazing, passionate, group of women. These past few weeks leading up to this soft opening this week you have all either jumped in last min or has been on for the long run. I am at a loss for words for the dedication of leadership, team bonding, taking charge where needed, and being the running support system that our Workplace Experience team needed at such a crunch time. I look around at this strong amazing set of women and thank my lucky stars to have you on our side as we step into this new chapter at our beautiful space. Thank you all and we appreciate your time and leadership. Keep shining through, as today might be international women's day but you all lead the pack all year long. Be proud of the ladies you are and keeping shining!\n\n31#Thanks To My Onboarding Buddies|Today marks my 3-month \"anniversary,\" so I'd like to thank all of you for helping me get off to a great start. You have been kind, empathetic, helpful, and fun to get to know and work with. I still have a lot to learn from you - and everyone - and I'm motivated to rise to the opportunity with you. Thank you!\n\n32#Powerful Reflection|Amy, there almost aren't enough words to express my gratitude for how far our relationship has come. The psychological safety you have fostered, moments where you've pushed me to grow, and the support to do so that you've continued to give. I take something new from every conversation we have. I deeply appreciate how we have grown together and am so lucky to have found you as my leader after all of the change I have been through. As I wrote my first reflection, I reflected on the challenges and accomplishments I have experienced under your guidance. Giving me the opportunity to reflect and feel pride for so many reasons was a powerful exercise. Thank you for leading the way you do, albeit challenging at times, it's pushed me to truly look within and learn so much.\n\n33#Prize is Right!|Thank you all for your participation in playing Prize is Right at Activate! While not everyone could win the grand prize, we appreciated everyone being willing to go up on stage and have some fun!\n\n34#ACTIVATE Appreciation|Taking a moment to express my gratitude to this incredible group! Each of you contributed to the joy, support and camaraderie I felt at Encore this week. From deepening bonds, making new friends, being a breakouts cheerleader, or trusting the cards process (if you know, you know), I was personally touched by your kindness, teamwork, and trust. Thank you and cheers to an amazing 2024!\n\n35#Respect for honesty, candor and proactiveness.|I wanted to take a moment to express my sincere appreciation for the exceptional work and dedication demonstrated by Amy Rice and Amanda Grady this week. Their partnership in kicking off discussions has been truly commendable, and I am grateful for their honesty, candor, and proactive approach.  Amy and Amanda's commitment to taking proactive steps to elevate Workhuman to the next level and secure key opportunities for Eric is exemplary. Their efforts not only contribute to the success of our team but also align with our collective goals for growth and excellence.\n\n36#Reorg? More like WEorg!|They say change is hard. Heck, it definitely is.  BUT‚Ä¶. when you‚Äôre lucky enough to have a talented, engaged, and supportive group of players in the mix to work through it, together, it gets a whoooole lot easier.     Over the past several weeks, I engaged you all asking for your time and insights to support us collectively working through the ‚Äúwho does what, now?‚Äù of it all. Along the way, I‚Äôve been continually impressed with how you all handled the work.  Each of you was clearly driven to make yourselves available amid all the other daily work. What‚Äôs more, along the way you all remained consistently engaged, thoughtful, open-minded, and positive in the face of working through the change.   Did we cure cancer? No. Have we solved every little thing that needs to be solved for? No. But we certainly solved for the vast majority of the most pressing aspects of the new ‚Äúwho does what‚Äù for our restructured creative teams. That is a major milestone and something we should all celebrate.   Thank you all for stepping up to help get this done, together. Here‚Äôs looking forward to starting of 2024 with what, to me, looks to be some of the strongest alignment we‚Äôve ever had regarding how our Marketing creative teams are structured and what work they each support. Upward and onward!\n\n37## Clutch - Commendable Comms|Amy, you‚Äôve been pivotal in constructing tailored communication strategies for a variety of business endeavors and audiences. Your adeptness in crafting briefing points for the ICG litigation, Pay Equity Comms, and the Financial filing all while skillfully managing our international PR agencies has greatly contributed to the success in how we navigate these uncharted waters. Your creation of an internal narrative that is honest, fair, and timely speaks volumes to your pulse on the employee,  dedication and perspective. Your strategic thinking, thoughtfulness, and unwavering leadership during challenging periods have been truly commendable.\n\n38#Content Strategy & Governance Committee Kickoff|And we're off!  Big thanks to this group for joining the Content Strategy & Governance kickoff, filling out the content questionnaire with valuable insights on content challenges and solves, and for the engagement and enthusiasm about improving content visibility, messaging consistency, integrated planning, content processes - and more!  We're doing big things with content strategy as one team and I'm grateful to each one of you.  Looking forward to continued collaboration in the months to come.\n\n39#Collaborative effort for '24 Marketing Planning!|Thank you team on all your ongoing efforts with the 2024 GTM Marketing planning process these past three months. Because of all your dedication to urgency and vast detail, we are in a fantastic spot for 2024 strategy and budget scenarios. We have taken our learnings from last year, adjusted accordingly from both a preparation and execution standpoint which has allowed our internal processes to continuously improve. You all came to the Integrated workshops ready to collaborate, identify potential gaps, having those healthy problem-solving conversations to build stronger ties and making decisions for a successful 2024. In addition, the technology and headcount asks tied to different scenarios was a big lift in a month‚Äôs time and we were able to solidify our business need well within our timeline. Amazing cross collaborative effort, thank you all!\n\n40#The Three Musketeers|While I think Richard was definitely right about us being a mighty team- he was only slightly wrong. We‚Äôre not a team of two, we‚Äôre a damn good team of three. While sometimes it doesn‚Äôt seem as obvious, it‚Äôs the three of us together that‚Äôs allowing us to make such an impact. I‚Äôm beyond lucky to work with the two of you and I would be lost without you both. I wouldn‚Äôt swap our team for the world. (I bagsy being Goofy)\n\n41#Launching Workhuman's first Star Search!|Sending so much appreciation to this team for the ideas and work put in to launch our first ever internal star search! Kylie - from jumping in on day one (which was also basically your day 1!) and taking the lead, to Jillian and Helly, for your internal comms advice and magic, Jen and Jill, your edits to copy and great ideas for how this search can progress and test, and Amy, for accepting the baton when I was in need of a pass. Thank you all for your teamwork - I can't wait to see what comes of this initiative! Thank you!\n\n42#Major Microsoft Integration Milestones|Last week was a big one full of major wins tied to the Workhuman integration for Microsoft Teams and I want to than you all for the huge role you played. Everyone in this group put forth amazing efforts to coordinate various promotions and support, including, the launch of an Integrations landing page on the new workhuman.com, press and blog announcements, a hugely successful session at Gartner London, and a crucial customer communications package. Each of you displayed your commitment to quality, teamwork, and our customers through this collaboration and I'm so grateful to work with you all. Here's to more to come!\n\n43#Company wide team work! üôåüèª|Thank you for taking time to support our team as we build out our new site experience for Workhuman.com. You provided us with guidance in your area of expertise to ensure our site is accurate & helpful for our users. Our website is the face of our company and we truly appreciate the time you dedicated to helping us drive towards a successful site launch! ‚ú®\n\n44#It takes a village|Every one of you lent your time, expertise, or both - and I just want to say THANK YOU! Your contributions are part of the DNA that powers the new workhuman.com, and we couldn't have done it without your help. It honestly took a village of extraordinary individuals to bring this project to life with a collective effort and shared responsibility. It was a massive journey to get here, and all of you had a hand in it at some point along the way. From myself, the team, and the marketing department - a huge THANK YOU again for your support!\n\n45#EMEA \"Content Strategy\" in the making!!|Hi Team, thank you very much for your contribution to the interview process for the EMEA Senior Content Manager position. I fully understand how time consuming the process can be, and I am truly grateful for your participation. The combined experience of this team has really helped to inform an educated decision across a strong candidate panel. We are delighted with our new team member who will of course be working very closely with you all. Thanks again from the EMEA team!\n\n46#Thank you|Hello all,  Thank you so much for all the collaboration, craic and kindness during my time in WH. You have been an absolute pleasure to work with across marketing, sales and cx where everyone works so hard to do whats right to continue to drive WH to success. Thank you for the strong support of enterprise architecture and at a personal level your tremendous support to me. I would also