d planning, dotting ‚ÄúI‚Äô crossing ‚ÄúT‚Äôs‚Äù, creating virtual, in-office, and in-person experiences, filming and facilitating Differentiator workshops, and more. You executed flawlessly, dealt with challenges without hesitation and ensured all our humans were informed with comprehensive communications throughout the event and fun well-thought-out games that allowed for maximum retention of our strengths. You created in-office experiences, provided an environment for everyone to thrive and engage, and you all put your best selves forward.  Thank you for always upping your game and never settling for the status quo. You did it and did it exceptionally well.  Thank you!\n\n65#Continued guidance and support|Amy-  I don't say this enough, but thank you for all of your support and guidance during my time here so far. It truly is a blessing to have someone like yourself in my corner to help me navigate Workhuman waters. I've learned a tremendous amount from working here and by working with you. You're a fantastic leader, and our team (and company) are very fortunate to have you.  Reid\n\n66#Fixed!|Ladies thank you again for leaning in to support last week and for making it such a quick fix. Really appreciate your partnership!\n\n67#Opportunities!|During the year each of you identified opportunities for me which pushed me out of my comfort zone. Thanks for seeing my ability to do these speaking opportunities and supporting me! Very grateful!\n\n68#Driving Women & Allie ERG Forward!|Sending you all a huge thank you for your invaluable contributions to the Women & Allies ERG this year! It has been a very exciting year, with Workhuman joining the 30% club and publishing data on pay equity and the gender pay gap, a fireside chat with Mary-Ann Sieghart, author of 'The Authority Gap,' in honor of International Women's Day, the continuation of W&A's bi-monthly virtual coffee connection, the development and launch of our \"How to be a Good Ally\" workshop, a Workhuman fitness 