ment of their teams with the pilot offerings of Developing Our Humans! These People Leaders learned how they can engage their teams using Workhuman tools, the Job Architecture, and Talent Development's resources. Thank you for taking time out of your busy schedules for these important topics!\n\n72#First Graduating Class of Spark Director+ !|Congratulations to our pilot class of Spark Director+, Workhuman's first-ever leadership development program catered specifically to our Director and Senior Director population! These 40 graduates completed a journey of self reflection, upward feedback, and personalized learning across 7 course offerings: Strategic Planning, Delegation & Empowerment, Emotional Intelligence, Cultivating Resilience, Leading Hybrid Teams, Psychological Safety, and Change Management. Thank you, graduates, for investing time in your own development!\n\n73#‚ú® Spark Director+  [Psychological Safety] ‚ú®|üí° \" Psychological Safety is a shared belief that one will not be punished or humiliated for speaking up with ideas, questions, concerns or mistakes.‚Äù ‚Äì Amy Edmondson.     üìä In 2012, Google embarked on a quest to build the Perfect Team. An initiative code-named Project Aristotle studied hundreds of Google‚Äôs teams to better understand why some stumbled, whilst others soared. Google‚Äôs extensive research corroborated the importance of Amy Edmondson's coined phrase, discovering that Psychological Safety is a paramount component of High Performing Teams.   ‚ö†Ô∏è Building a fearless organization that truly embraces psychological safety will leverage the benefits of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI), attracting and retaining a diverse environment of talented individuals, in addition to promoting innovation, connection, and a sense of belonging (DEIB).   üöÄ Spark Director+ is a self-discovery journey within an overarching Leadership Learning Track, offered to Directors and Senior Directors who manage teams of all sizes.   üì¢ Please join me in applauding our enthusiastic Workhuman Executive Leaders who participated in this month‚Äôs Psychological Safety module: Adam, Amy, Andrew, Colleen, Jason, Jeff, Laura, Linda, Martina, Michelle Drozdowski, Michelle Lane, Michelle McDaid, Niall, Rich, Tyler, Varun, and Zhennaa, thank you for your valued partnership as Psychological Safety Ambassadors. Warmest gratitude, Donna Louise Fitzpatrick.    üëâ FEEL FREE TO RECOGNIZE AND CHAMPION OUR EXECUTIVE LEADERS VIA THIS LINK: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/coachdonnalouise_google-projectaristotle-psychologicalsafety-activity-7006208407187681280-Pvxr?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop\n\n74#Collaboration at its finest|Kathryn and Amy, I wanted to take a moment to thank you both for being incredibly collaborative partners. The success of our webinars this year would not have been possible without you. You‚Äôve not only secured compelling speakers, but you‚Äôve been instrumental in setting up the story and foundation for each and every event, and have played a critical role in ensuring that every speaker was set up for success. Thank you for all the amazing work, for the collaborative spirit, and for being dependable, strategic partners.\n\n75#That's a wrap on 2022 live webinars!!!|Amy, Kathryn, Maya - I can't express how appreciative I am of all your support this year on webinars. Reflecting back on the past year and what we accomplished is truly something to be SO proud of. You all are absolute rock stars at what you do and I've learned so much from each of you. I'm so thankful to be able to work alongside such smart and talented people who are always putting out the best of best content to ensure we give our audience something meaningful! We finished the year strong with 16 webinars, 16!!! Those 16 webinars gave us a total of 35K+ responses, 11K+ attendees, 10K+ MQLs, 600+ meetings and over 100 opportunities valuing at ~$74.5M!! I'm so proud of this team and cannot wait to see the goals we crush next year. Thank you again for all your effort in making the webinar program a huge success.\n\n76#Making the Impossible, Possible|Marketing team and partners - Congratulations on achieving a monumental milestone of 50,000 Marketing Qualified Leads! By the numbers, this milestone represents two-year growth from 8,000 in 2020 to 50,636 (and climbing)! That‚Äôs an incredible 532% increase in demand growth in just two years' time!     The journey to this massive accomplishment started back in October 2021 with thoughtful and intense demand and brand planning, pragmatism of breaking big goals into smaller channel by quarter forecasts and plans, followed by superior discipline around performance management week on week, and critically aided by our partnerships with Sales Ops, Analytics, and Enterprise Architecture.     From web leads, to webinars, social surrounds, press amplification, Spotlights, and countless hours refining the leads scoring and ingestion models, this was a department wide effort through and through. As impressive as this achievement of goal (ahead of schedule) is, more than the outcome itself, it‚Äôs demonstrative of your collective discipline, collaboration, and commitment to quality execution. We‚Äôve learned much from this journey that will inform and enable success in fy23 and beyond.     On behalf of the Senior Exec Leadership Team, congratulations on making the impossible, possible!    -Tom\n\n77#Marketing Analytics Stakeholder Rockstars|In this season of gratitude, I'm excited to thank this team for your collaboration in all things analytics. Amy, you continuously find opportunities for your team to stay informed and find opportunities in the data we have available. Jenna and Simone, in our two years of working together you all have balanced your day to day things with keeping a strategic data plan in mind while also encouraging your team members to do the same. Tiffanie, your curiosity keeps us all motivated. And your commitment to contributing to the