ajor difference.\n\n112#Cool as a Cucumber|Amy - Since Day 1, you have answered every question instantly, with a smile and, without hesitation, taken the time to explain more than what I ask of you. Your talent and your dedication to Workhuman is remarkable. You always make sure Steve's best interests are at hand and always make sure I am involved. Your sorority poker face brightens my day. Thank you.\n\n113#Leading us to success!|A two-part shout out! Thank you for organizing such a great planning session, today and in June! The agenda was well organized & made it easy to stay on track + breaking out into groups was a helpful way to discuss challenges/collaboration opportunities. Secondly, I really appreciate your feedback style and you taking the time to meet one-on-one to discuss/review. I‚Äôm thrilled to be a part of your team!\n\n114#Coaching|Amy - Thank you for your support and coaching. You're advice consistently gives me a good perspective. It is always timely and helps me action things in an effective way. I appreciate your help!\n\n115#Thank You|Just a quick note of thanks to this amazing group of humans for coming together to produce a solid, comprehensive summary of Gallup report performance and activity!  There's no shortage of goodness in this report - from PR coverage to content production and activation across campaigns - all of which shows the magnitude of our collective efforts to position Workhuman as a thought leader in workplace recognition.  I'm so proud to be part of this team - and grateful to work alongside all of you.  Thank you!\n\n116#Cheers to our First Global Workhuman Partner!|Team, THANK YOU for being a part of closing our very first global partner at Workhuman: Qualtrics!  Each of you played an essential role in helping throughout this partnership journey.  Your help brought us to where we needed to be, which included: shaping the story, advising on the process and people that need to be involved, coordinating the meetings, bringing 