e that ROI. Thank you for investing in the planning process and each other this week. It may feel like we barely scratched the surface, but there were a lot of good discussions and new ways of thinking over our two days together. We have lots to dig into together but I'm excited! I appreciate being on this journey with this team. Thanks again!\n\n121#Collaborating to Deliver Quality|Amy, Wendy & Kathryn - a huge THANKS to each of you for the above and beyond, tireless support (especially as it overlapped with an already busy Workhuman Live schedule) and coaching over these past many weeks, allowing me to bring my best to our recent Evanta CHRO Keynote. And Lisa, a very special thanks to you for being so collaborative, helping me land finishing touches to my presentation. By all accounts, our session was well received and I couldn't have done it without you all!:)\n\n122#It takes a Workhuman village! (part 5)|Last week was the culmination of the efforts by so many to bring the Executive Forum to life at Workhuman Live. Joining the team only 6 weeks before the event, I was blown away by the work ethic, camaraderie, and creativity of everyone involved. Your support, encouragement, and tireless commitment to the finished product (both during the final stretch of planning and onsite) far exceeded anything I could have ever imagined in a team, and your efforts were instrumental in delivering an impactful program for ExF members. Thank you for bringing the vision to life. It was a sincere pleasure to work with you, and I look forward to our continued collaboration.  With the craziness of the event, I fell a bit behind with recognition in the final 2 weeks leading up to the event. Please know - your contributions did not go unnoticed.   Sarah M., Sarah B., Stacy, Chris ‚Äì for your strategic thinking on continuing the conversation with our ExF audience. Sarah M ‚Äì for attending the ExF sessions and crafting an informative and actionable blog post; Sarah B ‚Äì for compiling