ing fantastic talent for the show, to the ‚Äòon the Streets of New York‚Äô segment which I thought was a hit, to the carefully constructed questions and content to highlight the many opportunities and challenges facing HR today, not to mention the flawless streaming, it all came together extremely well and showcased our natural place as thought leaders and drivers of this important ‚Äòfuture of work‚Äô conversation.  Steve ‚Äì you handled the job of navigating the conversations with Laurie, Steve and yes, even the unscripted Gary Vaynershuk too, like an absolute pro.  I‚Äôm excited about the demand this event will undoubtedly drive in the final weeks of Workhuman Live Atlanta registration, and equally as optimistic about our prospects for more Spotlight events and format testing in the future.   Thank you to this cross-functional team of trailblazers and innovators, and congratulations on a fantastic event!\n\n145#Setting the Stage|Amy & Cara, Thank you for all your help and support working with the partner speakers.  These are a new category of speakers which also plants seeds for opportunities in the future.  Thank you for trying something new and different and seeing the connection of possibilities that link to the broader Workhuman!  Cara, you've done a tremendous job meeting with the various partner speakers and setting them up for success.  You provided the right amount of information and answered their questions.  They felt comfortable joining our event, especially in a world where we are just starting to come back in person.  You are also full of creativity in the different types of sessions they can have.  Amy, thank you for being an extension of the outside-of-the-box thinking!  Depending on the type of partner and topic, you helped walk me through different ideas and ways the partners could present and showcase their expertise virtually.  Several thought leaders had already signed up, and they're looking forward to being a part of it.  A special THANK YOU to both of you for this partnership and the ability to think BIG!\n\n146#Truly Amazing Teamwork!!!|After working for something for such a long period of time, it's fun to look back and think of all the little steps along the way that got you to the finish line.  We recently were able to bring Seagate into the Workhuman Family, and it wouldn't have been possible without this amazing group of individuals helping make it a reality.  Thank you all for your support throughout this incredible journey, which includes - prep for meetings, meetings, custom demo's, marketing campaigns, a micro-site, more meetings, more demos, value creation sessions, Workhuman Live Speakers, RFP preparation and submission, a trip to Denver, references, finalist presentations, follow up meetings, security reviews, pricing discussions, negotiations, and I'm sure a few more that I can't even remember.  It takes a herculean effort to bring in a new customer on board, and you are all truly appreciated...thank you, thank you, thank you!!!\n\n147#Leading the Way|Amy - I wanted to take a minute to recognize you for your approach to doing high quality work and holding others accountable to your standards. Being a leader is hard. Influencing others is harder. Influencing at Workhuman is harder still. You continue to do it effectively in a highly visible team without missing a beat. Thank you for being a great partner in helping to grow and evolve the market team and our approach.\n\n148#Gallup Dream Team ü§©|Amy, Jenna, Meisha-ann, Isha - As Gallup walked us through the initial amazing results of our research project, I realized I needed to give each of you a special shout out for your dedication and engagement on this project. Jenna, you've been my partner in crime on this since we first talked to Justin last summer. Thank you for always being available to talk through strategy, project management, internal pitches. And you're doing amazing work now to plan a huge PR splash come May and into the summer. Amy, you've been instrumental in getting this project approved and communicating its importance across the organization. You're also picking speakers and driving the executive steering committee feedback sessions. Amazing. Meisha-ann and Isha, you both have been with us for nearly every weekly touch base with Gallup, bringing your research expertise to the conversation and ensuring this new research augments everything you're doing in Workhuman iQ. I'm so grateful to all of you and so incredibly excited for the world to learn the business impact of recognition in just a few short months!\n\n149#Spotlighters|You are not the ones on stage. You are backstage working to make the spotlight shine on our speakers, guests, content, message, brand - all the things. Workhuman Spotlight - talk show edition is 2.5 weeks away. The recording is done. The work is far from done. I see you, working on this on top of your other work and our other events (Hello? Atlanta!). You are right on your spot doing what is needed. Thank you for your dedication, stamina, and commitment to the events, the team, the business. Cheers!\n\n150#Progress not perfection...|Amy and Brian - whatever would I do without you? THANK YOU to you both for your focused energy and time dedicated to all things WH Certified, to ensure the relaunch is a success! We made some big strides last week, thanks to your introductions and scheduling with key marketing, brand, and web dev colleagues. I appreciate your sense of urgency to drive our project plan forward to maximize the time between now and WH Live. Excited to be on this journey with you!\n\n151#In the Spotlight|Team, Wow! The Spotlight shoot today was amazing. As a team, we spoke a lot about due diligence and dotting our ‚Äúi‚Äôs‚Äù and crossing out ‚ÄúT‚Äù and today you proved that we did exactly that. We captured incredible content from well prepared speakers alongside a world class crew. It‚Äôs our collective effort that will allow this content and our message to spread across the world! Thank you for dedication, focus on quality, and commitment to getting us to this point. Proud moment. #progress. Thank you\n\n152#EAD 2022|Amy - Thank you for being a source of support, guidance, friendship, humor, and above all else the power of NO for the past 3ish years. Of all the valuable tidbits you've shared with me, I will take away the practice of writing down things when I notice them. It's something I used to be in the habit of doing frequently and thanks to you, picked up again in the past year or so. Being able to visually reflect on where you've been allows you truly realize where you are in the present moment. It creates a space for you to recognize the beauty and the growth that exists in the here and now. Appreciate you!\n\n153#How can I help?|That's what you ask almost every time I tell you about a challenge.Thank you for being so willing to jump in and solve problems. You are so generous with your time, expertise, and problem solving ability. I am so grateful for every conversation; your POV always makes me think - you make me better.\n\n154#Ukraine Communication!|Wow! We could have done nothing like our competition - but that is not who we are or why we exist. In under 24hrs this group mitigated brand media risks, developed internal and external Comms in support of Ukraine, gained buy-in for WH to match 20K worth of donations, and drafted our company position on the terrible situation occurring in Ukraine. You united together, placed egos and hierarchy aside to impact millions who need it the most - As Kevin said, always assume positive intent and lead with our core values of respect!\n\n155#HR Leaders Teamwork|Thank you both for all your efforts on the HR Leaders Workshop program.  Amy, you recommended interesting topics that were both important to the executive audience, but also unique to previous workshops, and therefore positioning Workhuman as the leader in the space.  You were also instrumental in getting