success of marketing analytics.Go team!\n\n163#Q1-derful!|Amy, Laura, Gavin, Katie, and Julia - I wanted to highlight and recognize the comprehensive and collaborative demand generation plan you and your teams have put in place for Q1! It reflects the hallmarks of our 2022 Marketing Strategy: fewer, bigger integrated campaigns, anchored on key themes, and designed for leverage and re-use! These plans span brand, ABM 1:1, and programmatic demand campaigns. We are well positioned for success and growth as a result of your teamwork, leadership, and careful, longstanding planning work done in the trenches of Q4 2021! With gratitude, -C&R\n\n164#Let's Go!|Amy, I've been incredibly impressed with the leadership, work ethic, and resilience. From leading your team, solving challenges head-on to driving the development of channel-specific strategies for SEO, Social Media, Earned and Paid PR, and Content Marketing, you have set a solid foundation for a great FY22 and we're already making significant progress toward our strategy board goals. Thank you for focusing on the end (results) while supporting and stewarding the team on the development of the initial plans. Keep your eye on the prize(s)!\n\n165#Thank You for Everything|Amy - As I start to transition to WHiQ full time, I wanted to say thank you for your mentorship and guidance over the last 2+ years. You have been such a great advocate for me and my work both in SEO, and more recently, in analytics. Thank you for being a sounding board and a partner as we expanded our SEO strategy, brought on an SEO agency, and created the brand dashboard. I'm really looking forward to working together in my new role to build on all the great things the team has been working on and will work on in the coming months!\n\n166#Team Connection and Cheer üåüüéÑ|Thank you Amy, Jenna, and Simone for organizing an energizing and productive external comms get together this week. It was so refreshing to meet in person and see everyone's lovely faces. Human connection really is critical! And the secret Santa exchange was a really fun way to get to know each other. Cheers to more connecting and collaborating in 2022. ü•Ç\n\n167#Communications Partners Extraordinaire|A big thank you to this mighty team of communications professionals for being fabulous partners in crime in 2021! We came together this year like we really haven't done before. Thanks to your leadership, Amy, you collaborated, recognized the need for deeper partnership, and organized the team to support our biggest customers with great co-marketing opportunities, valuable speaking opportunities, and set us up to have repeatable success in multiple formats. Our customers feel the partnership shift. Our Strategic Client Directors feel the partnership. Thank you to the whole team for stepping up, proposing great ideas, supporting great ideas, and delivering incredible content for all to leverage. We are better aligned to deliver the right messages at the right time, deliver the right speakers for the right opportunities, and really organized for the team to strike in the right moment. Many sincere thanks to each of you for your expertise and energy and commitment! Big things to come in 2022!\n\n168#Cheers to you!|Amy - Thank you for an incredible year of support, realness, and overall growth. You have led the external comms team through some massive wins this year. Creating new functions, huge media hits, onboarding agencies, moving away from processes that no longer serve us, adopting new ones, and always‚ÄìALWAYS‚Äìfocusing on communicating with the team as much as possible. I have never worked with a leader who is more open to share information across the board as you, all in the name of keeping us informed for the better of the business. Something you've taught me since I first began reporting to you, last year and when I started reporting to you again this year (LOL), was to write down when you are trying something new. \"Life moves pretty fast. If you don't stop and look around once in a while, you could miss it\".  This Ferris Bueller quote comes to mind when I think of your advice here, because it's true. We move so fast in our day to day, that if we don't take the time to stop and look at where we are compared to 1 month or even a year ago, we will never recognize and appreciate the growth. It's a simple exercise that has a huge impact on confidence and appreciation for the journey. Thank you for an incredible year of growth, connection, and support. Grateful for all you do!\n\n169#Lights, Camera, Action!|Thank you all for taking the time to come into the office on a Monday and be a part of the video for McGraw Hill. Consider this your official Oscar award from me for best background actors for a textbook video ever! I so appreciate the teamwork and the time you took out of your busy days to help.\n\n170#There is a Superhero in all of us|Blown away again by his team's commitment to dropping everything to come together and use their collective talents to drive the business. Here's to all of you in celebration of teamwork!  When it matters most, we step up, rally the troops, and march right into the battle headfirst. Yesterday was another great example of what happens when you bring great minds together, the sparks fly, the ideas flow and suddenly we have a solution. There is a Superhero in all of us, we just have to put on the cape. Cheers to the team!\n\n171#Gallup Research Project Exec Prez!|Amy,  You evaluated and negotiated the Gallup Research project, united a cross-functional team to plan and kick it off, led your team to manage specific components of the deal, and more.  You recently presented the overview of the project to the SELT where you received significant praise on the overall value of the package and we're just getting started. The outcomes from the project will be instrumental in our business. Keep leading - you making a significant difference.\n\n172#Webinar Extraordinaires!|Julia, Amy, and Laura - I appreciate your outstanding teamwork to develop and deliver our most recent webinar featuring Merck's successful application of AI-driven in the moment micro-coaching (or Inclusion Advisor as we like to call it). You achieved over 700 registrants and garnered great response from a key prospect account, UPS, I wanted to highlight as part of this recognition moment:  - \"That was EXCELLENT!!! ... I downloaded the presentation, and am forwarding it to a manager in DE&I for further discussion.  I‚Äôm working to make a recognition platform a reality, as you know, so the more additional business units support this effort, the better! ... have a great Holiday Season.  I‚Äôm looking forward to 2022! Kindest regards, Jamie Werner, CRP | Ancillary Benefits | UPS\" - Moreover, you've set us up for more leads this month with the additional webinars planned. This is great momentum to take with us into 2022, so we hit the ground running, and keep our \"Without the human it's just work message\" \"always on\" in the market. With gratitude, -C\n\n173#Thankful to be on your team!|A wild year made easier because of your compassion, empathy, and leadership!\n\n174#Allyship in Action|Sometimes it gets exhausting when you're always having to call things out. But on this day, you two stepped in and did it. I can't say enough how much that means to me. Not only were you upset on behalf of others who got left out of the antiracism blog article and the lack of representation, you did something about it. This is what true allyship looks like. I am honored to know you and glad to work with you. You both make Workhuman better. Thank you so very much.\n\n175#Thankful to Be on Your Team|Amy, just wanted to send a note of gratitude for your steadfast leadership of our team. I can only imagine the amount of slacks, meeting invites, calls you have on any given day. Yet you always make time for the team, prioritizing 1/1s, sharing relevant company info, and so much more. You're always looking out for what's best for the team and clear on priorities so we can focus on what really matters. I know not always easy so I want to say I really appreciate that and I know others do as well. Thankful for you!\n\n176#Scenario Planning Sesh #1 was what I'd call a Win|My head is spinning from all the inspired thinking in today's planning meeting. Thank you for sharing your Plans on a Page <or is it 'Plan on a Pages?!'> with the broader team. Thank you for deep diving into some of our Marketing priorities to identify integration points, gaps, opportunities for testing, and more. It was awesome to see different people gather to collaborate cross-functionally and spend time thinking about the \"what if sh....scenarios.\" And lastly, thank you for being good sports about the ice breakers questions. From Buzz Lightyear to time machine travel, childhood crushes  and early retirement dreams, I learned a lot of new things about each of you today!  And yet, I am sure you all agree that it felt like we barely scratched the surface in our three hours today. Not to worry! This is the starting point and I have a good feeling that this was just the first of many Scenario Planning sessions to come. So strap in and look forward to next steps AND the next invite. I am excited to work together to ensure we are set up to deliver business results, feel proud of our work, and have some fun along the way.\n\n177#Planning for Purpose!|Team,  What an incredibly informative, purposeful, and quality team-building day! Thank you for being present and prepared, for sharing your FY22 department vision and goals, and for collaborating on a unified FY22 brand marketing plan and most importantly our guiding purpose as a leadership team. I feel energized, optimistic, united and supported, and look forward to taking on the challenges that FY22 will bring.\n\n178#The goal is progress, not perfection!|‚ÄúFirst steps are always the hardest but until they are taken the notion of progress remains just a notion and not an achievement‚Äù ‚Äî Through a time of transition, new planning processes and forecasts, and current executional needs this team has been exceptional. You‚Äôve come together, forced needed changes, asked the right questions, and most importantly you‚Äôve done it as a team. Thank you for leading by example, overcoming the daily challenges, and for accepting new perspectives and approaches.   You are building our game plans now so we can all enter the stadium with confidence together next year.   Remember, The goal is progress, not perfection\n\n179#Customers are internal too|I would like to award Amy, who took time out of a busy schedule, to offer her expert guidance and knowledge that will help me with a project that I am involved in. It would have been easy to push a meeting out to another time, but the respect shown me as an internal customer is fantastic and merits recognition. thanks, Neil\n\n180#The Long Term Solution|Amy and Nick, thank you both for preparing and facilitating an insightful overview of our SEO strategy today and our future focus at the Exec Progress Meeting. Nick, the significant growth of the Workhuman SEO landscape has been dramatic over the past two years - your technical knowledge, due diligence in managing multiple internal and external SEO fields, and your focus on key metrics have been phenomenal to watch and now see in our performance. Amy, your leadership here is clear - driving our discoverability from PR, Content, SEO, and Social is no easy task, and how this team is coming together and unifying tasks is incredible to witness.\n\n181#Thank you for keeping it real...supported!|Amy, thank you for continuing to support me and my role on the comms team, especially during the past few weeks. I appreciate our honest, solutions-focused discussions and the actionable plans that we walk away with.  To say that we are operating a machine with a lot of moving parts right now is an understatement, so thanks for leading 