continue onboarding in the midst of continuing all of our other responsibilities.\n\n186#And thats a wrap!|Thank you for bringing your brilliance, remarkable talents, expertise, creativity, innovative thinking, and skills to drive the successful execution of the Spotlight broadcast and WHLive registration launch.  The work for these projects starts months in advance and continues for weeks after we go live. Over the last several months, there were endless moments of comradery, collaboration, and a continuous drive to raise the bar.    The road was challenging, but despite the obstacles, YOU DID IT!  You delivered a fabulous production and flawless launch.   Your passion is contagious. Congratulations and celebrate the moment!!\n\n187#Leading the way!|Jess, John, Richard, Chris, and Amy - thank you for putting together a great Brand All-Hands. I have heard from many folks who loved hearing from their colleagues and seeing all the great work being done.  What is also clear: we are a team who is committed to each other just like we are committed to excellence.  Thank you for leading the way today and every day.\n\n188#\"IRL practice\" for a \"Virtual success\"|Team - Outstanding to see all of you come together today to conduct final prep and plan for our Oct 6th Spotlight Broadcast. It is clear you all are laser focused on a great experience for our customers. Keep up the great work! With gratitude, -C\n\n189#If Slack Speed Dial Existed...|I would have you on it! Last week I was struggling to show up, process and get work done. We were chatting all things work and you made a point to ask me, how are you? And took time to listen to my oversharing, offered some free time to chat live about it and encouraged me to keep going but also pause if I needed to. I didn't call you (whoops) but knowing that I could gave me the energy to finish up the day, enjoying the evening with my family and remember that tomorrow was a new day. Thank you for your support and your willingness to listen.\n\n190#Supporting Women - WSJ!|Congrats Jenna and Simone on a strong piece of coverage today in the Wall Street Journal! In regards to hiring Abby when she was 9 months pregnant, Amy was quoted in saying, ‚ÄúRather than worry about the stage of their pregnancy, more employers should hire women for who they are and who they can be.‚Äô‚Äô I'm beyond proud and honored to work beside every single one of you strong women working to lift up other women in the workplace!\n\n191#WSJ!|Amy, thank you for: 1. Being a badass working mom, 2. Being open about your experience being hired while expecting and hiring expectant moms, 3. Telling your story to the WSJ! Not only did this story allow us to build rapport with a top tier journalist, but this online & print piece helps Workhuman's brand awareness. Again, THANK YOU.\n\n192#Leading with humanity!|Thank you, Amy, for your ongoing support, counsel, and strategic leadership that you provide our team.  You are readily available to help streamline processes, balance workload, and ensure that the speakers bureau is working as efficiently as possible.  I appreciate all of the support you've provided me since I started my new role in June.  Thank you for your commitment to quality, teamwork, and embodying Workhuman's values.  Cheers!\n\n193#Reaching all who need to know|Thank you to this wonderful team for your collaboration in getting our follow up comms reviewed and out to those who need them. Amy and Tyler, thank you for bringing up this important next step in our comms cascade - reaching those who have joined us via contract, but not started yet. And to Lauren and Christina for thinking about what to say in interview with candidates and getting that wording just right. And to Kerri for reviewing the messaging and and Katie for also ensuring the access to Workday and instructions were worded accurately. Teamwork for the win! I hope the resources are helpful as you now begin using them with your candidates and new hires (and those on leave!). I appreciate your responsiveness in helping us get this done quickly and in such a high quality way.\n\n194#Extra, extra! Representing our humans!|Thank you so much for your quick support as an extra for our Chronicle filming this week. With not too many of us humans in the office, YOU rose to the challenge to help represent us and our amazing culture. Can‚Äôt wait to see your smiling faces on TV!\n\n195#Award-Winning Chronicle: #1 in New England/US TV|Reid,  thanks to your grit and determination, you secured Workhuman on Chronicle! Thanks to you, we get to share our amazing story with a captive New England audience. Chronicle is not only the oldest and one of the most popular and awarded local magazine TV shows in the country (out-ranking all other in terms of audience growth YOY), it is the #1 watched in New England - with audience growth across all demographics that consistently out-performs all others in the country. It's not easy to get coverage on this highly popular long-running show - and you did it!    Now everyone in New England who works for a living - or loves someone who does - will know what it means to Workhuman.   Amy, thanks to your incredible set up and your leadership with Reid, a new teammate, Baystate Health will bring to life a thriving culture of recognition. They are heroes, in the 4th Wave of a Pandemic, who are willing to take time out to share what it looks like to Workhuman and why, during the hardest of times, social recognition has made all the difference to their employees and the communities they collectively serve.    WAY TO GO, TEAM!  Thrilled with this new phase of PR for Workhuman. Congratulations!\n\n196#Making Magic at Merck|Team, it‚Äôs been an exciting journey launching Inclusion Advisor with Merck. In the past few months, we‚Äôve worked closely with them to get a presentation proposal about our IA partnership created AND accepted for World at Work. Cue months of careful planning to get to this point in the journey, when we‚Äôre invited onsite to record their presentation. Beyond that, their glowing words on their recognition experience, the impact on their employees, and their advocation of IA, the list goes on and on. As we watched Michaela and Christopher present today, it was pure magic. Our clients speaking authentically about our partnership and they‚Äôre so grateful for the support they received. Don‚Äôt just take my word for it, Michaela and Christopher wanted to thank you personally since they couldnt recognize you directly through their own INSPIRE program.\n\n197#Keeping the Conga line going!|Amy, Jenna, Chris ‚Äì thank you all so much for jumping into the Conga line and being so enthusiastic about hearing their recognition story. I am thrilled you were able to meet the team today and hear directly from Wende and Adrienne why Conga Stars will play such a pivotal role in their business success and company strategy. You brought your energy, experience, and passion for getting great stories out to the market, and as I‚Äôm sure you would all agree, it completely energized the Conga team. The opportunities for sharing their story and it‚Äôs growing narrative are endless, and I cannot wait to see how brilliantly you all bring it to life. Thank you for taking the time to meet Wende and Adrienne today, being an excellent partner to me as a navigate this new territory of customer work,  and growing this important partnership!\n\n198#Winner, Winner, Chicken Dinner|Team - Congratulations on all of your hard work with Workhuman's submission to the 2021 HRO Today's Baker's Dozen Award program.  Because of you, Workhuman has claimed the #1 spot!!!   You should feel very proud of your work.  As the #1 Recognition vendor on the planet, we are able to launch a global brand campaign and acquisition campaign to educate HR leaders and practitioners about the urgent importance of making work more human.  Take a bow. You earned it.\n\n199#Without the human, it's just work|Jess,