 on helping us get to where we are today. It's taken a few rounds of word-smitthing, updating fields in Sprinklr, and getting new team members trained on utm's, but I am happy to see that we're now in a good place to be able to launch this new process next week! This level of detail and tracking is something we've never had before (at least on our owned channels) and I'm bleeping pumped for the insights to start rolling in. Thank you team utm-awesome!\n\n203#Respect for Quality QBRs!|With the pace of business and everything on our plates, it's easy to want to just keep your head down and march forward...However, it's important to stop, look back and evaluate the past. With the right mindset, the past offers lessons that can influence the future - helping us work smarter, make better marketing investment, strengthen our process, refine our messaging/creative and ultimately shape what we will test and optimize next. We wrap the 2Q'QBR up on Monday and I wanted to say THANK YOU to each of you for the time and effort you put into documenting and sharing key insights from your respective areas of marketing expertise. QBRs are an important part of the planning cycle and I am grateful for your commitment to them.\n\n204#Can't Thank You Enough|Thanks to the best and most talented team for making taking a vacation with my family so doable. Each of you went the extra mile to keep all the \"things\" going. On behalf of myself - and wife and kid - thank you. Now if next year you could somehow work with Mother Nature to make it less rainy.\n\n205#Dreaming of Dashboards|Amy & Nick, thank you for taking the time to walk through the bureau's Q2 reporting. As we continue to evolve our reporting at every level, it was very helpful to understand where we can double down and where we can pull high-level insights. I look forward to telling a more comprehensive story of how our speaking engagements impact brand marketing and the business.\n\n206#You can‚Äôt buy this on Amazon!|Amy, From 