ng Leave More Human!|Thank you so much for helping me onboard and dive right in to meaningful work. In my short time here I've been simultaneously onboarding and planning for a maternity leave. I've received nothing but support and genuine well wishes, while still getting my hands dirty with important work. I've only been here a couple of weeks, but this is the most seamless maternity leave I've taken thanks to the support of my own team, recruiting, and benefits! I cannot wait to get back into the swing of things after my leave!\n\n211#Content Crusaders|Amy & Jill, while this seems overdue from the May event, it‚Äôs top of mind for me. Coming back from maternity leave, I‚Äôm in awe of all the work you both took on to ensure the content at Workhuman Live Online was a success (and it was with a 4.7/5.0 rating!). This is not an easy area to jump into. There are relationships to form, quick deadlines to hit, and many moving parts. Thank you for the time and energy you poured into these sessions in my absence. You‚Äôre a huge part of the reason I was able to enjoy my time with baby Jules this spring.\n\n212#Rockstar Panel|Hi Team,  I want to send out this recognition moment to thank you for the time you spent interviewing candidates for our Newest Social Media Specialist addition to the team-Micah Lucas. Each of you brought valuable insights which helped me as I continued to hone in on what we needed for this role and I enjoyed working with each of you throughout the process. Jon, congrats on your first hire here at Workhuman. Looking forward to the amazing things this team will continue to accomplish.\n\n213#Supporting the Women At Work ADP webinar|Thank you all so, much for the support, help, preparation, ideas, inspiration and so much more in getting me prepared for the Women at Work ADP Webinar. I was thrilled to represent Workhuman at such an important event, and take my responsibility as a male ally very seriously.  I would not have been able to do the job without