th each one of you! Let's do it again tomorrow!\n\n218#Twinning on Innovation, Collaboration, & Mustaches|Amy, First of all thank you for brightening my day with humor and knowledge!  You were a delight to meet with.  You certainly added a 'bow on top' to make the day even brighter!  Also, thank you for sharing your deep knowledge and expertise around how we work with some of the consulting firms from a Comms and AR/PR perspective.  I enjoyed building ideas and the art of the possible together.  Thank you!\n\n219#Conference Planning!|Well, where do I begin? We are officially on countdown to two of our largest conferences of the year which so happen to be within days of each other. Easy right? Well, for this team it comes naturally. Thank you to each of you for playing an integral part in the planning phase of this busy season and helping to make it such a success. Angela, you are the dream project manager. As soon as that project request goes through you are on it! Setting up tasks in Workfront and scheduling our kick-off calls to go through the details. Lauren, Alana and Liu each of you are essential to creating the catchy copyright and creative artwork to accompany our virtual booth and profiles at the conferences. Amy, Jenna, Simone and Reid have played a crucial role when it comes to organising and scheduling our keynote speakers as well as our overall messaging. Thank you to each of you for supporting us and here‚Äôs to the kick off of the conferences!\n\n220#Pioneering the Human Workplace|Thank you all for your months-long efforts in creating Workhuman Live Online. Together, you showcased the importance, impact, and transformative power of putting humans at the center of the workplace.    Doing that took the cooperation of teams across Workhuman, including Technology, Product, Workhuman iQ, Sales, Customer Strategy, Customer Service, Finance, Legal, HX, and Marketing. It was a tremendous effort, and in turn, I am immensely proud of what we accomplished.   I know there were difficult moments during the broadcasts, so I want to specifically call out the resolve and focus many of you demonstrated in supporting our customers and prospects with rapid-response access to key content.    While I would say, ‚Äúthat‚Äôs a wrap‚Äù the truth is this is just a beginning‚Äîthe response has been overwhelmingly positive, and I look forward to seeing the impact it has our company‚Äôs growth in the future.   Ultimately, the greatest demonstration of the power of working human is all of you. So again, thank you for the commitment, hard work, and humanity you brought to Workhuman Live Online.    With gratitude, -C\n\n221#Upping our PR muscle|Team - these past few months have marked a monumental shift and up-leveling in our PR efforts and impact.  Together with bringing on a new agency, you have laid the foundation for Eric to build a strong relationship with the WSJ among others, and you landed the incredible interview he did with Josh Johnson from MSNBC on Friday night.  It was a fantastic interview and loved how much Josh was engaged in the conversation.  These are exactly the kinds of things we need to achieve, building from one powerful outlet to the next - and you did it with grace, determination, imagination, and grit.\n\n222#More Rewrites than a Hollywood Movie|Amy - Thank you for your help crafting a message. Your insights were incredibly valuable. I appreciate your partnership and support.\n\n223#WHLO Exec Forum Goes Digital!|It was a pleasure collaborating with you all on the WHLO executive sessions, boldly going where no WHL exec session has gone before - virtual!  Thank you for your strategic ideas, flexibility and dedication to the success of the sessions.  Thanks also for the timely laughs along the way!  Great work for such an important audience!  Cheers!\n\n224#Leading with Empathy|Mihai, Jen and Amy, THANK YOU for sharing your insight, vulnerability, candor, tips/tricks, and so many real examples of how you address the challenges that often get in the way of leading with empathy. As we were prepping for the session I thought, if managers can walk away feeling like they can breathe a little easier because they are not alone, that would be a win. I know they walked away with much more than that. The chat was on fire. Just a few of the comments: ‚ÄúSuch wonderful learnings and so needed, today and every day.‚Äù ‚ÄúThanks for taking the time to reflect, gather your thoughts and for sharing .... really good to have this practical workshop in this session.‚Äù ‚ÄúAmazing job MJ, Amy, Jen, and Mihai!  All of you were so vulnerable and inspiring.‚Äù  You did such a wonderful job providing specific examples, and building on one another. I tied this recognition to \"respect for all\" - for valuing one another's perspectives, and the perspectives of all of our people leaders listening in. I am so grateful that you gave your time and energy to this discussion. Thank you, thank you, thank you!\n\n225#All the right moves|Ladies, I have have been so honored to work with you on the WHLOL Executive Forum. For months, you have all prepared for these two hugely important sessions and every decision has been made with a commitment to an excellent experience, compelling content, teamwork, and respect for the program and to one another. It really has been a privilege to work with each one of you on this.\n\n226#Fastest keynote|Team, We just launched the second keynote speaker for Workhuman Live Online. You did it in record time. From negotiating contracts, making quick decisions, developing copy and creative, speedy approvals, building, trafficking, launching, coordinating schedules. We even recorded Common's session before we promoted him. That's a first! Common and Zain were prepped for a relevant conversation to close the event and drive home our messaging. Then on to editing. Oh my, so much editing to filter out the best of all the words. It takes a dedicated team of individuals with unique skills to include a keynote in an event. Thank you for your commitment to Workhuman Live. I recognize all the work you do behind the scenes to make it seem... common.\n\n227#Impressive|Anne and Amy,  In speaking with the PR leader for ATD, she shared that Rebecca (CHRO) was super impressed with her experience on the panel.  Her quote was....  \"in all the virtual events I have done, this was the most impressive team I have ever worked with. They take it to a whole new level\"    I can't thank you enough for all your hard work on the upcoming WHL event.  You made such a positive impression on her, and I am sure she will share it with her network.  She left the experience thinking Workhuman is first class all the way.\n\n228#Not Common At All|Congratulations on an outstanding fireside chat between Common and Zain. Your speaker prep and emphasis on our key messges came to life thoughout the entire conversation. Recognition, honest and actionable feedback, DE&I, and real life, relevent stories shine throughout this keynote. I cant wait for our company and our attendees to see the result of your great work.\n\n229#Launch of Hootsuite Amplify!|Today we launched our new employee advocacy program, Hootsuite Amplify! This 8 month long project touched a lot of teams and required tons of communication, collaboration, and attention. I want to recognize all of you for your support along the way that helped today's launch go as smoothly as it did. This is the first and an incredibly important step to becoming a social first organization. Thank you all for your contribution, patience, input, and dedication to the program's success.\n\n230#Interview Crew: Assemble|Team, I wanted to recognize you for the time and rigor you put into interviewing final candidates for the content team role.  Not only did you commit to multiple conversations and feedback sessions, you also fostered an authentic and vigorous dialogue that got each candidate excited to join Workhuman.  On top of that, we were able to