r all your tremendous work in delivering a top notch Gratitude Summit for the Johnson & Johnson Global Educators.  This was a great opportunity to motivate their team, work to instill a culture of recognition, showcase what the Workhuman is all about and highlight the many ways Inspire has become a focal point for a number of their people activities.  Chris and Samar, you were both amazing partners at this event and I'm thankful to have had the chance to work with both of you.  The content you delivered was so well received and it was done flawlessly.  Your deliveries were just natural and free flowing.  It felt like a true conversation with their team.  Traci, once again you showed why you are just a true professional and expert in creating memorable content.  You are a story teller who has a feel for the audience and how we want to get the points across that will resonate at an event.  Thank you for your support and guidance as we were preparing for this session.  Amy, thank you for jumping on this opportunity with lightning speed and helping to make this session a success.  You seized the chance to get in front of this global team and we now have potential events to expand our connections with the J&J teams.  I am thankful to work with such an incredible group of professionals who excel at what you all do.\n\n243#Educating Global Education Leaders|Traci, Chris, Jay and Amy!!! What an amazing group of Humans who delivered an extraordinary and powerful session on the Power of Recognition and Gratitude for J&J's Global Education Solutions Group. The feedback from the J&J team has been phenomenal and we are already hearing from key stakeholders on \"how informative it was and how leadership wants to drive the empowerment of their employees.  Also the survey results are all 4.5 / 5 stars and above so far\". This outcome puts us in a super strong position for further collaboration and partnership as we continue to support J&J in charting a more work human course.\n\n24