ld up by all humans involved! I'm excited to see where our imagination and determination take marketing analytics.\n\n253#Energy + Passion = Contagious|You were on our eComm call today you did a presentation where your energy and passion for the brand is very apparent. Being a very new hire it was exciting to see and be a part of. Thank you!   Also, the notion of loud kids is something I relate to the core.\n\n254#Workhuman Listens|All,  It‚Äôs been such a pleasure to talk to you all over the past weeks, and to hear how much the voice of our customers matters to you! Over the coming months, we will help you create surveys to tap into the wealth of great things our users have to say about our products, how positive their experiences are‚Ä¶ how they feel using the platform!! We have distilled the conversations we have had into a roadmap, which we will share with all of you next week. Over the past year, we, the EXM team, have seen some heartwarming testimonials from users, and I have no doubt that we are about to open the floodgates of thanks! I recall about a year ago, when we did our first proper ‚ÄòPeriscope‚Äô that the resounding response was a 72% ‚ÄòJust plain THANK YOU‚Äô  and the remaining 28% had some really encouraging and helpful feedback to offer, which we can use to make our product even better!!  All we need to do is listen!  I am excited to start working with you, and encouraged by your enthusiasm for the program.  Let‚Äôs build Workhuman listens!    Brian, EXM team\n\n255#Caring Matters!|Z and Amy, Thank you for organizing this Marketing team during our most recent meeting.  Everything was clear, the topics were key priorities and everyone participated.  And you demonstrated how you are about each of us. Thanks you for your exquisite leadership!\n\n256#Partnership|Amy, Thank you for your ongoing partnership with the customer acquisition team. Over the last few months, we‚Äôve had multiple conversations ranging from how our teams can work together more 