utions, work with our schedule, and be a trusted team member.  Thank you, Simone, for your ability to pivot and find creative solutions to making this process as seamless as possible.   Ray, thank you! You are always there any time, day or night.  It is such a pleasure to have you on our team to solve any problem, big or small, with a smile and a laugh.   It is such a pleasure to work with you guys, thank you for all your support.\n\n261#ONE TEAM.|Amy - Thank you for your partnership and collaborative approach. Every day your actions and words show your commitment and respect for ALL. You just reached out with a meeting request to a cross functional marketing group to proactively form a brain trust around WH IQ. \"How do we unlock all that good data and get ahead of it?\" Then I went to Slack and you had just shared an HR.com article with an interview with Steve P that you thought would be useful to our team. In our Monday standup yesterday, you took time to ask the right questions to ensure we were all aligned and properly supporting the Product Marketing on the upcoming Community Celebration launch. Not only are you clear, focused and confident, you are consistent with your ONE TEAM approach - and we'll be a better team thanks to all that you do. I see you and appreciate the positive impact you have on all of us.\n\n262#Rowing in the Same Direction|Thank you for always being strong advocates for Employer Brand! I appreciate you taking the time to review upcoming campaigns that are happening on the corporate side, and thinking about how Employer Brand can align to these themes as we engage our candidate audience - so our corporate and employer brands are both rowing in the same direction. As we look to make Workhuman a household name - aligning our messaging and themes when speaking to both prospective clients and prospective employees is essential for us to show the whole picture. Appreciate all you do!\n\n263#Team Updates|Amy - Quick note to say thank you for continually pushing us to be better, even with something like our team updates. You gave everyone a chance to weigh in on how we could improve the format and topics during our last meeting of 2020. Then followed up during holidays. And then, a third time, gave us a final chance to weigh in via. email during this first week back in the New Year. I know we're still semi transitioning to this new format but, it was a great first meeting of the year and I'm looking forward to testing out new ways of communicating. And making this year great with the best team ever!\n\n264#Vision, Clarity, and Collaboration...|Z and Amy - this award is long overdue. In the past several months, you both have taken the reigns on major marketing initiatives, goal planning, directors meeting agendas, leadership alignment... the list goes on and on. You've supported each of us by pushing ideas, clarifying objectives, and keeping us all focused in the same direction. This is the glue that holds all of our teams together, and helps our our marketing efforts (and ultimately our brand) become greater than the sum of its parts. This is NO SMALL TASK. And my words here don't do it justice. I'm writing this, on day 2 of the new year, where I'm already seeing a further increased level of clarity with our team meetings and objectives, and its so great to kick the new year off this way. Thank you both for everything you have already done, and will no-doubt continue to do.\n\n265#Putting in the work|Team - on behalf of Patti and myself, we wanted to say, \"Thank you\" and recognize the teamwork, collaboration, and effort you've collectively put in to moving our Pulse Survey action plans forward from Q4 2020 to Q1 2021. Together, we've made great quarter over quarter progress due to your efforts. This is an \"above and beyond\" initiative you've stepped up to lead. In doing so, you are each playing a leadership role for your marketing colleagues and peers - and - making a meaningful contribution to Patti an