\n269#On Wednesdays, We Meet, We Talk, We Think, We Act.|And then we do it all over again the following week. I am grateful for your commitment to our Marketing Leadership call week in and week out. Sure, we might not have 52 weeks on the books for 2020, but we MOST DEFINITELY have twice that many hours and then some between our regular weekly meetings and our virtual offsite time together. Focus group of 1 here, but I find the time we spend together immensely valuable - hearing about what various teams are working on, gathering different points of view, discussing ways we can work better together, learning from each of you as subject matter experts and awesome marketers and humans...and last but not least, strengthening the connections between us even though we have been working apart since the early days of March. Enjoy a couple weeks off and we'll assemble again before you know it! THANK YOU!\n\n270#Have time for a phone call?|Amy, thank you so much for the amazing collaboration this week. With new folks on your team and an evolving content team; I was concerned about the 2021 goals and ensuring we keep momentum. No hesitation, you made time for a call during your morning routine time to collaborate together and walk through concerns, talk through different perspectives and offer some actionable next steps. Thanks for being so willing to partner and just talk it out, you are an awesome colleague and friend!!\n\n271#Continuing to set the standard for greatness|I wanted to thank all of you for the amazing work you've done honing our message and user experience on the Workhuman Certified website. As we move forward with this initiative we are gaining so many insights through our data collection and market testing, and having an agile team ready to respond to these learnings is vital to our success. Each of you has shined in so many ways under a tight timeline to get this site ready for re-launch, not to mention having a major holiday right in the heart of our development timeline!\n\n272#Grateful for all you do!|As this time of thanks rolls around, I wanted to express sincerest gratitude for you. Having worked together on recent projects I have seen how you go above and beyond for every task, which shines through the end results. Have a wonderful, happy and safe Thanksgiving. I'm looking forward to continuing to work with you in the rest of 2020 and beyond!\n\n273#Fearless Captain|I am so thankful for your mentorship, leadership and direction. Things move quickly here and you're always available to answer questions, provide feedback and give guidance. I'm constantly learning new things from you and I am so grateful for everything you do. Thank you.\n\n274#Fearless Planning!|Z and Amy - thank you both so much for the amazing work putting frameworks from Patti and Chris into action in our marketing planning process. This has been an immeasurable amount of work, and being remote without whiteboards and flip charts makes it all the more difficult. You both have taken this on and helped us all prioritize and make the time, all while developing a process that keeps us engaged, collaborative AND productive! I'm so thrilled for the alignment and stoked to see what comes in 2021 as move into hypergrowth-mode. Cheers to you!\n\n275#Lights, Audio, Action on the Big Stage!|Kevin, Amy, Jenna, and Jon - the Brene Brown webcast is a tremendous win for all of us.  The stage this represents for our brand is global and beyond the walls of industry.  The conversation topics are so right on and do a magnificent job of telling our brand story, starting with our founder. There is no better B2B tech company on the market than us.  You and your teamwork are instrumental in paving the path to let everyone know what it means to Workhuman!\n\n276#Stepping up our PR game|Jenna and Amy, Amazing work in identifying 3 potential new PR agencies that can get us to the next level of brand exposure.  Your respect for urgency without losing your sense of value, 