ur collaboration, support, all-in attitudes, and LEADERSHIP! To the Moon and Beyond!\n\n291#Do you sleep?|Amy, this appreciation moment is for you being a wealth of support at all times and hours. While I prefer not to Slack you or reach out after normal business hours, it happens and you‚Äôre always available. I greatly appreciate you taking the limited time you had today in between calls to walk through the flow of a deck with me only to rejoin the conversation once your calls wrapped for the day. Thanks for making the time.\n\n292#Supporting the AWS Analyst call|Thank you all for the support, answer edits and keeping me between the lines on the AWS Analyst call.\n\n293#Hello Workday!|Thank you for being an early adopter of Workday and for completing your scavenger hunt by the end of our first day officially live!!\n\n294#The book is here!|Thank you, Amanda and Amy for quickly connecting with me to get the word out to employees about the book being out in the world and ready to share. You both quickly reacted and helped get a message ready to share with employees. Many thanks to you, Amanda, for collaborating in record time and posting the news to employees. As you can see from the reactions, a happy bit of news that people were excited to hear! Thanks so much.\n\n295#Leading the way forward|Amy, your efforts around the Making Work Human book launch have been impressive to witness first hand! I admire what a good leader you‚Äôve been as I was onboarded to the project, which was full steam ahead! This launch isn‚Äôt to be taken lightly. There are dozens of moving parts and you‚Äôre on top of it all! I googled what it means to be a good leader and felt this was very fitting for you. Thank you for continuously providing clarity, being decisive, keeping everyone informed, being responsive, putting your trust in myself and the team, and doing it all using good energy which fuels others in a positive way.\n\n296#7 Habits ‚ÄìFramingham Graduates ‚ÄìClass of June 2020|‚Äú