"298#\"Recognizing promise and progress\"|Teamwork makes the dream work. There‚Äôs no \"I\" in team. Together everyone achieves more. The cliches are all true! Brenda and I heartily thank you for your tremendous partnership these past several weeks as we worked through and finalized the go-to-market assessment and integrated marketing plan for Workhuman Certified. While a tough process at times, you all persevered to ensure we had the right answers to why are we doing this; why should others care; why now; and the most important of all: is what we are doing really ready for prime time? The three of you have truly been the driving force, asking the right questions, choosing the right words and setting us down the path for success. I know our work is far from over, but we‚Äôve achieved a major milestone that will pave the way for so many other work streams to begin. Thank you your collaborative spirit and respect for teamwork. Brenda and I look forward to continuing this journey with you to help change the workplace for good!\n\n299#With colleagues like you...|Z, Amy, and Chris - thank you for your leadership, preparation, and delivery of the amazing first Marketing Leadership Team offsite.  The agenda, format, pace, and time keeping kept us all focused on what is important: cutting through the noise so we can grow our customer base, our share of wallet, and our brand. Your dedication to our team and our mutual and individual success is inspiring.  Thank you for all you do for us.\n\n300#Always willing to lend a hand!|Amy, you're always willing to make time to give advice, listen to ideas, help with questions and ensure we're putting our best foot forward. Your guidance is extremely appreciated and valued!\n\n301#You are Certifiably AWESOME!|Team, this award could be given under any one of the Workhuman values. Despite set-backs presented by COVID-19, the mixed levels of Workhuman institutional knowledge, and with the advent of new GTM and Integrated Launch approaches, each of you lended your passion, your insights, and your voice to the holistic GTM Assessment phase.   The world's best and most innovative teams truly do Workhuman!  Onward!!!!\n\n302#Yang to my yin|In Chinese Daoist thought, the yin and yang are used to think about how seemingly opposite forces may actually be complementary, interconnected, and interdependent. The yin embraces the moon, the passive, the emotional, and creativity while the yang represents the sun, the active, the rational, and planning. In a workplace, yin is all about learning, knowledge, discovery, and playing with ideas while the yang is brilliant with establishing markets and putting strategy and structure in place. Working more closely with you over the past few weeks I've seen how critical you are to taking the ideas and putting them into a structure that makes sense. You are the yang to my yin and I‚Äôm truly looking forward to our continued partnership to take all the ideas and learnings to the next level.\n\n303#For supporting the IASA Web Summit|Thank you so much guys for all the help in promoting the IASA global conference. Public speaking at industry tech events is so important for everyone, and your support and guidance makes it 100 times easier.  Thank you for the social posts, the copy and all of the help and advice.\n\n304#Measurement for success|A bit late but I wanted to thank you all for your dedication, collaboration, and teamwork as we solidified measurements for Awareness, Perception and Preference. Learning and listening to each other through every meeting, I saw such great passion for accuracy and full transparency in the unknown. We worked together to present solid recommendations, and received great feedback. With our next steps to operationalize, use Q1-Q2 2020 as litmus on measurements, and prepare for QBRs together we'll create the best measurable Brand marketing we've ever had. I couldn't be more proud of this team.\n\n305#Listening Post|Amy, I wanted to recognize months of collaboration.  I know in your role as one of of the MSOs, you hear many voices every day. With that in mind, you take time to reach out and ask for input. (Even when you probably think I won't agree with you!)  I'm sometimes not the loudest voice in the room (call?) and sometimes I don't speak, even if I think I have something valuable to contribute.  As I continue to find my voice, your approach makes me feel valued, respected, and helps build the confidence I know I need to bring to everything I do.\n\n306#The future is now. The future is working human.|Team - this group has been the nucleus for \"what's next.\" You've ripped up and thrown away the rule book for what was. You've embraced the freedom, liberation and inspiration that comes from having a blank sheet of paper to operate from. Yes, we've been grinding the last two weeks, but we are on the precipices of exciting concepts that will propel our brand and business forward. Keep pushing, we're nearly there. With gratitude, -C\n\n307#Pioneers Unite!|Team - Thank you for your unyielding focus and energy in our \"first ever\" digital planning session for 2H '20 and Oct WHL-S initiatives. This was an epic-ly long virtual offsite that uncovered and unlocked critical new and innovative thinking for representing our solutions as \"essential\" and \"compelling\". Thank you for 100% commitment to this session and the ensuing outcomes. Lots of powerful thinking and actionable next steps to fuel our high growth, marketing making, and bleeding edge tech company and brand. With gratitude,  -C\n\n308#Smooooooth transition|Katie, Amy, and Dario - thank you for making the transition of paid social to Customer Marketing so seamless.  You came together to create a solid plan that sets us up for continued success and exponential growth.  Although our structure is now different, our opportunity to grow together and create magic in our market is better than ever before because of the three of you.  THANK YOU for all you do.\n\n309#Such a great partner!|Amy, thank you for looping me in early on the momentum press release and for getting me up to speed on all that was happening. You were a great collaborator with me in finalizing the internal comms plan to share the news. I'm thankful for your review, advice, and support in finalizing all the messaging. And, for all the laughs along the way!\n\n310#Press Coverage|What a great first week of the Momentum release! Congrats to you all for an incredible level of coverage and interest. It certainly feels like a real breakthrough in the Irish media. We‚Äôve never had this level of recognition and depth of coverage. We also covered all the basis with meangingful coverage in all the right online and offline publications, subscription services and radio stations. Well done!\n\n311#Cutting through the noise|PR Team,  I am so proud of the work you have done for the transaction.  Your maturity, persistence, and commitment to excellence despite the many speed bumps and challenges that we know as the reality of PR, demonstrates perfectly that imagination, determination, and resulting innovation that is so critical for our amazing brand. The sky is the limit for what we can do together.  Thrilled with your work and honored to work with each of you!  Congratulations on a great release week!\n\n312#A to Z and back again|Amy - this has been a long time coming but I wanted to say thank you for your partnership. I value the collaborative relationship we've built over the last several months as we have linked arms to lay the foundational groundwork for our MSO functions. We still have a long way to go but I am grateful that I have the opportunity to be in this role with you by my side. It feels good to know you have my back and I have yours and when we can't both be involved in a meeting, project or task, we can count on each other to \"cover\" and run with it. I had a rough April with two major losses in my family and you were there for me...checking in to see not only how I was feeling but asking what you could take off my plate, insisting that I lean on you so I could heal. I can't tell you how much that meant to me. As we start to put more disciplined marketing planning in place, we constantly ask ourselves, how can we streamline the process, become more efficient, tell a more cohesive story, future proof our programs? I appreciate the iterative approach we're leading together and am genuinely grateful to have you as a partner and friend. Thank you!\n\n313#M-S-Oh ... My!|Amy, Z - Thank you for leading an outstanding Marketing Strategy and Ops discussion today. I know Patti and I are excited to have your leadership and organizing skill set to help drive transformation. By anchoring around KPIs, Key Initiatives, and a Prioritized Marketing Calendar you are helping us build necessary rigor and discipline to unlock the full potential of our world-class Marketing engine. Thanks for leading from the front. Excited about what's to come. With gratitude, -C\n\n314#Doing Great Things|Amy - There is so much I want to say in reflecting over the last two weeks of getting to work with you but, I will focus on this: YOU ARE AWESOME!! Thank you so much for taking the time to listen, to learn, and above all else to guide me in the right direction with a growth mindset. I've already learned so much from you and feel empowered to do things.. GREAT things that will take our social media presence to the next level while contributing to business objectives. Looking forward to the future and so grateful to have your support and leadership!\n\n315##WeWorkhuman|Amy, thanks so much for putting together an eventful team day on Friday. We started off with a strategic meeting to align on priorities and metrics as a newly formed global comms and social media team. We ended the day with a (global) scavenger hunt that allowed us to get outside. With kids, parents, and pets in tow we discovered and shared our most scenic views and more. During my adventure, I even found a community garden that I had no idea existed. I guess that‚Äôs what happens when you get outside and explore! On behalf of the entire team, thanks for an impactful day!\n\n316#A calendar a day...|... Might not keep the doctor away, but does help us be organized as a leadership team! Amy, Z - thank you for being relentless in your pursuit of our shared marketing calendar for town hall today. This is the critical example of discipline and organization we need to accelerate progress and balance smart trade offs in the ever-evolving market we exist - thank you for leading the way and setting a great example for the team. With gratitude, -C\n\n317#Valuable Leaders Share Knowledge|Amy, I wanted to say thank you for all of the knowledge you've shared with me over the last few months. Even as we transitioned to remote working, you never missed a beat to identify areas where you can lend support. You‚Äôve taken my 6:30 p.m. calls to help review work even though that‚Äôs vital time with your family and girls. You have shared media interview tip sheets and training so I can ensure important conversations stay on track around our messaging and main points. You always keep an eye out for interesting speakers and call for papers forms to send to me. There are too many examples to list but thank you for always sharing your knowledge and experiences so that we can all continue to grow.\n\n318#Telling a Cohesive Story!|Amy and Z - wanted to thank you both for the great work you do each week to roll up the director updates into a thoughtful and cohesive story for Chris and Patti to share with the larger leadership team. It's not easy taking all that content and weaving it together quickly and efficiently; making it look easy!!!! Thank you for all you both do!\n\n319#Shepherding Thank You Healthcare|Amy - You have done a wonderful job steering the Thank You Healthcare program, developing cross-functional plans with all of our marketing stakeholders. The program has been a unique one, targeting consumers for the first time in Workhuman history! This has not deterred you and you see the opportunity in every turn. Thanks for your leadership!\n\n320#Supporting external speaking engagements|Amy and Rob. Thank you both so much for the support you have given in both presenting and helping prepare me for external speaking engagements in the last month, both with Atlantec Festival and the upcoming opportunities in Dublin.\n\n321#Fierce commitment to urgency|\"We are now faced with the fact that tomorrow is today. We are confronted with the fierce urgency of now. In this unfolding conundrum of life and history, there IS such a thing as being too late. This is not time for apathy or complacency. This is a time for vigorous and positive action.\" - MLK JR.   Team, since I started just over a month ago, I have heard from many of you and our stakeholders who have talked about the misfortune of joining Workhuman during a global pandemic that has changed every thing about how we live: from how we interact, to what we spend our time and money on, what we value, and how we work.  The truth is, there was no better time for me to be able to witness the magic that is Workhuman. We already know what is important and that is human connection. What you have demonstrated is humanity during a time of extreme urgency - a rarity in life and certainly in business. Thank you for your passion for your and your commitment to each other and our stakeholders.  I am honored to work alongside each of you.\n\n322#Moodtracker Launch success!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for delivering our brand new Moodtracker product. Thank you so much to everybody for the amazing work on the Moodtracker product. Hard to believe this was just an idea at the beginning of January. Since then a team has formed, the product designed, architected, built, tested, branded, communicated, marketed and launched. Whew. The speed at which the groups collaborated is a tribute to the sense of camaraderie and positivity we have at Workhuman. The energy, imagination has shone through in every way. This coupled with the determination to deliver a world-class product means that today we have a sixth edition to our Workhuman Cloud suite. Welcome Moodtracker. On behalf of all of the humans in the company, thank you. Eric.\n\n323#The Social/PR Powerhouse behind Moodtracker GTM|Amy, Jenna, Katie, Holly, Max, Roshni and Dario, this was my first chance getting to work with a lot of you, and I can‚Äôt thank you enough for the amazing work you‚Äôve done getting our message out to the world for Moodtracker and the Workhuman Livestream post event strategy. I feel like I learned a lot from each of you about the process and best practices for getting these ads into market on a variety of platforms, and I‚Äôve been so impressed with your creativity and professionalism during these campaigns. I know this is only the beginning, but I can‚Äôt wait to see what we‚Äôre able to pull off in the weeks to come!\n\n324#Our Survey Says - You are Fantastic!|Colleen, Amy & Niall, I wanted to thank you all for all of the support you gave me recently with my dissertation research. I really appreciate you taking the time to review the survey, it was great to get all of your input, and and I'm really thankful for all your help in getting this approved. Thanks again :)\n\n325#Leadership, Guidance, Support|Amy - I am grateful for your leadership, especially over the past weeks. Thank you for checking in with me every week and for bringing the team together to make sure we all stay aligned. You've managed to keep us all informed as priorities shift, you've kept it real and kept it positive - which I appreciate. Most recently, you provided helpful guidance to help me navigate a couple of challenges I was facing and provided a helpful bigger picture as well. I know it can't be easy leading others while balancing so many big initiatives, but you've stepped up to that challenge and I'm so appreciative. Thank you!\n\n326#Making us stronger together - every single day|Team - what a week! I am blown away by your collective and individual innovation. These are the experiences that can give us the best learnings and insights - not only in terms of skills, but more important, learning just how much awesomeness we are capable of bringing to the world. Thank you. Onward!\n\n327#All systems go!|This group rallied mid week in an incredible pivot from soft launch to just LAUNCH within hours. I cannot thank you enough for the commitment to urgency for launching media campaigns.\n\n328#Quick Response Team!|Amy, Dianne and Lauren - thank you all so much for your quick work helping out with some content for the customer launch of Thank You Healthcare! You all have the fullest of full plates and still sprung into action to help the customer team. The content for the message was excellent and just what we needed to help the team get messages out quickly. You are all awesome teammates!\n\n329#Lifting us all as you rise|Without batting an eyelash, you both jumped in with your hearts, your brains, and your brawn to create an integrated plan to help us elevate the spirits of the healthcare community while giving each of us an opportunity to share our deepest thanks.  Watching you each lead, bring out the best in each other and the rest of us - it is a thing of beauty that is making a huge difference.\n\n330#A Warm Welcome and A Supporting Hand|Amy, thank you for all you've done in the past couple weeks. You've answered every one of my questions, helped me prioritize activities and gave me space to complete onboarding. Even though starting a job from home isn't ideal, you've made sure I'm in the know and connected to the all the right people and are doing a great job supporting me as I navigate this new role. I could not be happier to work for you.\n\n331#Checking In, Checking Success!|Amy, Dan, and Katie - Every morning at 9 since we've been at home due to COVID-19, we've checked in together with our video calls.  You've shared not only amazing ideas and suggestions but also worries and concerns as we navigate so many interesting paths as a company, culture, and team. Thank you for your willingness to be so open, as it's a critical ingredient for trust and ultimate success.  And boy, has there been success!  Incredible achievements across PR, content, and social.  Anyone looking at our social feeds can see your work and leadership on a daily basis and see how it's propelling our brand and company higher and higher. Thank you for all of your work (and teamwork) as we continue to show how Workhuman can help elevate human connections across the world!  Kevin\n\n332#X-Team GTM Collaboration Success|If you would have asked me at the beginning of March if we could bring a new product to the market in a few weeks I would have laughed. If you told me we'd all be doing it remotely because of a global pandemic I would have told you that you were crazy. Despite all the challenges this team was able to rise to the occasion and do what I would have thought was impossible. Coordination is always challenging, but this team managed to do it all in sweatpants (I hope we've all given in) on Zoom, which is remarkable. Thanks for the amazing work team!\n\n333#Delivering the Human Touch|When the COVID-19 pandemic began to accelerate, our marketing instinct immediately went to providing a human face on our content. There is no more powerful thought leadership than humans speaking with humans ‚Äì sharing experiences, emotions, and best practices on how best to craft a path forward in these unprecedented times. That was the inspiration for the daily video series, ‚ÄúKeeping Work Human,‚Äù which launched last week amid the flurry of everything else we are working on. James and Matt ‚Äì you stepped up and deftly handled the logistics of turning a Zoom video conference call into usable, shareable video. Pam ‚Äì you project-managed the overall logistics, setting up the invites, and showing agility when we had to pivot. Amy ‚Äì you immediately energized your team to schedule guest speakers. Mike ‚Äì you were at the ready to transition the videos to Workhuman Radio podcasts. Sarah and Jess ‚Äì you stepped up to write the question frameworks and provide a content resource. John and Diane ‚Äì you saw what was happening and introduced better discipline and process. Jen ‚Äì you were our first guest and dazzled our viewers with unique leadership best practices to manage remote teams. And Steve ‚Äì our host ‚Äì your ability to set the tone, and keep our guests at ease with your authenticity and humble heart, is what makes it all work. We‚Äôve only just begun ‚Äì and we have a busy few weeks ahead ‚Äì but I couldn‚Äôt be prouder of this team and the messaging we are bringing to market.\n\n334#It‚Äôs a Balancing Act|Amy, I wanted to shout out your incredible leadership during these ambiguous times. I‚Äôm not sure how you fit as many meetings into the day as you do but at the same time you‚Äôre helping to keep the rest of us afloat. You took the time to understand how each of us prefers to communicate and receive feedback prior to the COVID-19 crisis. This started with ‚Äúhow I like to work‚Äù probing questions you provided to the team as early as Ignite. Fast forward to now where remote working is the standard but luckily we‚Äôre not starting from scratch. I feel 100% supported and in the loop on all new projects even if I‚Äôm not directly involved. You‚Äôve checked in daily to get a pulse on my workload and how I‚Äôm feeling in general. While these are challenging times for everyone, it also brings out the best attributes in people. Thank you for your support, transparency, and leadership. You‚Äôre a master balancer of all the things!\n\n335#It's Go Time!|Team - I wanted to first say thank you for your rapid response to the business's need for a COVID rapid response campaign. I also want to acknowledge that working at this pace and with a level of uncertainty may be new and/or uncomfortable, but that has not stopped this group from leaping into action, mobilizing, and being agile and responsive to rapidly evolving priorities - including stopping existing work, pivoting planned content, and being open-minded about new ways of working team together and team apart (as we leverage remote technology for the next while). Still lots to do, and I'm confident with the cohesion demonstrated this week we will do great things that help our current and future customers navigate uncertain times and that we will unlock new approaches and agility as a cross functional team. Thank you all. With gratitude, -C\n\n336#A tough day, a great team|Each one of you exhibited all of our values today but I chose Respect for All because we had a lot of decisions today that required us being in agreement and with a path to move forward very quickly and everyone did it in a respectful, efficient way. This was not a fun meeting - we all love WHL and are dedicated to it being perfect. Today, though we were taking it apart, was no exception. Everyone concentrated on the right message for our audience, thoughtfully went through all affected segments, and delivered a great plan. I'm so proud to work with each one of you and hope we are back together very soon planning '21!\n\n337#Team Corona|Coronavirus.  Covid-19.  A giant headache.  We all call it something different ‚Äì especially because the situation with it has been changing minute by minute and making our decision making process so challenging.  When we made the decision to create new content and FAQ‚Äôs for our Workhuman Live site and audiences at 8PM on a Friday night, I crossed my fingers we would be able to activate.  We needed to get information out to our audiences that was clear, consistent, and valuable to ensure they felt informed and at ease.  No surprise ‚Äì every single one of you stepped up.  Dianne was slacking me almost immediately with project set-up details and timelines.  Lauren had copy in my hands before 6:00 AM (you actually sent it at 1:30!?!)  Chris and Amy were both there to review, edit and get on the phone to talk it through.  Jon had site pages staged and new pop-up functionality built and staged Saturday morning.  Jen and Anthony had layouts and content ready to deploy.  Jill was providing copy strategy and reviews.  Holly and Anne were standing by ready to act as needed for our audiences.  And Lauren ‚Äì our guiding light and champion of strategy supporting the whole process was as responsive as ever with reviews and feedback.  This is such an evolving and fluid situation, but the team never ceases to amaze me.  You gave up family and weekend time to help ensure our customers had the information they needed, when they needed it.  Your continued dedication and respect for customers, urgency, quality, and teamwork is amazing.  Thank you ‚Äì and Cheers to Team Corona.\n\n338#First Class Collaboration|Team! I wanted to say congratulations and celebrate the collaboration that infused our FY20 Marketing Strategy Board. As of this past Friday we have an aligned, crisp, and clear plan for Marketing's focus and KPIs that sits perfectly between the Company's goals, objectives, and major priorities. I also want to recognize the diligence that went into to making this be a plan that effectively spans Customer + Brand Marketing and reflects alignment with our key partners (SLT, CS, CX, and Finance). It is metrics driven to ensure accountability and through it's more streamlined nature, now infinitely more shareable with our teams and partners. Look forward to rolling this out to the teams through all hands these next two weeks and continuing to revisit it for focus, alignment, and relevance to the business's needs as our business evolves. Love to see the positive momentum and teamwork modeled to produce this output - lets keep it going. With gratitude, -C\n\n339#Action and a Plan|Z, Amy - I wanted to recognize your rapid response to the needs of the business and the people needs of our marketing team. The new approach you brought to our wkly Dirs+ meeting was powerful. I found it to be agenda-driven, aligned with our FY20 goals, and hyper-focused. Thank you for quickly evolving away from \"old ways\" of doing things and demonstrating leadership around taking a new approach while being open to feedback and continuing to iterate as we fine tune the format. Keep up the great work - it's making a difference that matters. With gratitude, -C\n\n340#Now that... is a meeting|Amy and Z - I am so impressed by the work you both have done to get our directors meeting into a really great place. We had an awesome agenda, kept on time, the team was focused and we all walked away with good info. Collaboration at its finest. Thanks so much for taking this on and making it the best meeting I have had all week! Cheers to you both!\n\n341#Last minute ask|On top of your day jobs, I asked each of you to present in our weekly marketing directors+ meeting today - without a ton of notice. You produced slides, shared great content, and kept the team engaged during your sessions. Thank you for embracing the new format for our weekly meeting which we tried for the first time today, and contributing to what felt like one of our best meetings to date!\n\n342#Helped me find my voice, quite literally!|Publishing my first article in Forbes was big moment for me and ironically, all the things I shared quite literally were a part of how this came together. Amy, thanks for the steady push to share my voice. You have been a staunch supporter guiding with a firm yet gentle hand. Lynne, you got the ball rolling, talking with me, helping make sense out of my myriad thoughts and seeing a story, putting them in writing in a great cohesive way. Dan, you steadily provided guidance and resources. Dave, you leaned in immediately when you heard my frustration, rolled up your sleeves and channeled my voice through rounds 4, 5 and 6. Sarah, you are just magical with your editing style. You took version 6 and over the weekend edited for crispness and polished in a way that made me feel eloquent and clever. I am grateful for this agile team that came together to ironically help me find my voice in print! Thank you all for helping me take my own darn advice: taking that first step. Here's to many more!\n\n343#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n344#Thought Leadership Excellence|It‚Äôs one thing to discuss thought leadership and it‚Äôs another to deliver it ‚Äì which each of you has done with editorial aplomb. ‚ÄúThe State of Humanity at Work‚Äù not only showcases results of a provocative survey of 2,613 full-time workers, but takes the data and brings to life some of the uncomfortable issues that companies are facing in the new decade. Core human needs like safety, fair pay, work-life harmony, growth, inclusion and belonging, and recognition are covered here ‚Äì with startling results.  Sarah ‚Äì your storytelling ability is outstanding, humanizing the data in a way that brings the issues to life. Greg ‚Äì our resident Einstein ‚Äì your data-carving skills and guidance to ask the questions in the right way set the tone. Carrie ‚Äì your design ability is always worth pointing out. The report is simply elegant. And Amy ‚Äì you had the idea to go beyond the annual report and deliver research in time for Employee Appreciation Day ‚Äì leveraging our agency to augment internal efforts. Well done to each of you and thanks for your commitment to outstanding thought leadership.\n\n345#Constructs for success|A few weeks ago we took on a herculean task, gathering a small cross-functional team to create a rubric for consistent messaging heading into 2020. 19 core narratives, from themes to products, and the building began. Each of you played a part, both large and small and we are off to a such a strong start! Next steps are culling these down even more to get them over the finish line but I couldn‚Äôt have done any of this without your help and support. GO TEAM!\n\n346#Interview dream team|A sincere THANK YOU to all of you for your participation in interviews over the past few months, for our Director of Product Marketing. Someone of you met with 5 candidates - which adds up to a LOT of time out of your schedules. Some of you only met with a couple of finalist candidates, but helped us to wrap up the search and make important decisions about who we were hiring. Overall, you all were so responsive, flexible, open-minded and just a pleasure to work with throughout this process. Thank you so much for the part you played in getting this fill across the finish line!\n\n347#Umbrella gratitude|Thank you all so much for your collaboration with our Dublin based Umbrella project. From the messaging to the design, you were always there to help and enthusiastic to lend a hand wherever needed. Thank you all.\n\n348#HIRED!|Amy - thank you so much for your partnership on the PR Manager search! It took longer than we anticipated, but I so appreciate your flexibility, candor, and timeliness throughout the entire process. You were always quick to reply which is so important in a tough market like Boston - and you were always quick to offer words of encouragement - even when things weren't going our way. Thanks for sticking it out with me, and congrats on your new hire!\n\n349#The dream team does it again|Before too much time gets away from us, I wanted to thank each of you for your incredible work on Ignite Dublin. Within one week there were a LOT of moving parts. LIKE... TONS. And never did this team flinch. Everyone stayed focused, helped in any way possible and kept on top of those million details to deliver an incredible event (with handwritten notes being adjusted just in time... I'm looking at you Mrs. Grady!). Such an awesome undertaking and I loved working with you all on it!\n\n350#High Scores for Content|Amanda & Amy, during today‚Äôs Evanta lunch & learn, the representative from Gartner showed a slide that shows Workhuman speakers at Evanta events score higher than their average session score. That shows firsthand that the messaging and presentations you're putting together are truly resonating with the c-suite audience. As always, great work!\n\n351#Great panel questions!|Thank you so much for your excellent questions for the panel.  Very thoughtful questions each, thank you for representing the audience so well!\n\n352#MSO for the win!|Amy & Z - Thank you for taking ownership over the Thursday Marketing meeting. Under your guidance, the meeting went from scattered and jumbled to organized and productive. I appreciate you both stepping up to drive the agenda and the meeting!\n\n353#Certifiably Great Marketing Deck|Amy - great job on your work around the marketing plan for Workhuman Certified. An initiative involves a great many ideas and people. It also involves strategic thinking - with an eye towards what will be most impactful for the business. It also involves pushing for the right elements and ensuring alignment across a team.  It can often seem like an uphill climb but the progress is quite evident to all involved in the project. There are great things ahead in the market.  Thank you for all your efforts!\n\n354#Content team rockstars|Can you be our team on every project? Seriously, MJ and I had the dream team of collaborators when it came to working on the content for our ambitious agenda. Amanda ‚Äì we really don‚Äôt know how you do it, you‚Äôre some magical unicorn of creative genius mixed with speed and quality, and always quick with a smile and a joke to keep us all humming along. You created the on-screen visuals for a huge portion of the event. From all of Derek‚Äôs material to the awards, and both Alice and Jesse‚Äôs presentations, you were a force! Thank you for the incredible work. Amy, Clare, and Kristen ‚Äì a huge thank you for being there at every turn with ‚Äúhow can I help?‚Äù, ‚Äúwhat can I do?‚Äù and then making things happen. From helping select and assign panel questions to supporting our main stage speakers and breakout session leaders, creating and delivering desk drop surprises, and sharing great feedback on the event, you played a critical role in what was a great couple of days in Boston. Next, on to Ireland! Thank you for everything!\n\n355#Taking the workhuman rocket to new highs!|Amanda, Colleen, Mary Jo & Amy, I am fortunate and proud to work with you this past few weeks.  Congratulations on the part 1 of 2, great success that you delivered in Boston this week!   You were the foundations to my presentation and mc work.  Without your guidance, direction, ideas, detailed content, slides, notes, cards‚Ä¶. I certainly could not have done it!  With great appreciation for being right there at all the stages (sitting beside me too!), it‚Äôs a real honour to work with such professionals, and a high performance team as you all are.\n\n356#Keeping marketing leaders on task for 2020|Amy & Z - Shout out for shepherding the marketing leaders along the 2020 planning process. It's hard to create a format which can fit everyone and everything we do. There are always nuances. But you listen to feedback and make wise decisions as to what is needed and what is not needed to build a well-structured plan. This is especially difficult since there are 2 new VP leaders on the horizon. You've stepped in to fill the need!\n\n357#Hidden Heroes, Team Focus|All - I wanted to thank you for all of your collective work on an upcoming keynote announcement for Workhuman Live 2020. I greatly appreciate your focus and diligence to getting the package complete and ready for speaker approval. As we all know, approvals can often take more time than we'd like - but your ability to get this package done in a timely and high quality way is amazing. Well done to all of you and thank you for your efforts. Can't wait to see it out in market!\n\n358#A New Horizon|Thank you for taking the lead to get us together in Dublin, updating us on the latest thinking as to how the brand strategy is evolving, and for exploring opportunities for how we capitalise on that in the local market. We are big supporters of the work you and your team are doing, and keen to be advocates for brand alignment. Thanks also for turning us into fantasy characters, in order to build new skills and awareness.  I really appreciate the trust and openness you show towards us, and how you listen to our needs, which incorporate the local market, and the cultural differences between Ireland and the US. I'm very excited about the potential and benefit to be derived from stronger partnership between the Marketing and Technology teams.\n\n359#What we are all about|Amy,  from Oran, Niall, Rosana, Rob, Shane and myself- \"THANK YOU\" for today.   Your session was informative, insightful and very helpful.   You took what could have been a tough topic and helped make it fun and engaging.  I have never seen such active participation in role play :) and it is attributable to the quality of your training.  We are all incredibly glad that you practiced to your taxidriver audience,  despite him almost driving you to an alternate venue where you might receive the help you need :) I leave you with famous words(slightly altered)  that sum up how we all feel  \"...Watch and you'll see....Some day we'll be....Part of your world\"\n\n360#Perspective|Amy - I wanted to let you know that I value your support in helping to develop the next wave of leaders here at Workhuman. You have taken many people under your wing (both at the direction of the HR team and on your own) and provided them with a valuable lense on the organization, how to manage through it, operate in it, and how to grow themselves. Even though this work is focused on developing others it does come with learnings for you as well, both good and bad. The work you're doing is important. Keep it up.\n\n361#Giving it your all|Amy - I‚Äôm recognizing your for all the work you put into this year‚Äôs holiday card email. From the initial brainstorm, to charities, to expanding this year‚Äôs card beyond customers only, to gathering feedback from Alice, Kevin, Kristen, Eileen, Pam, Jill, Mark, Anthony, Stacey, and the list goes on and on to ensure the execution covered all parties appropriately. We realized the benefit of versioning it out for prospects and set it up through Yesware for reps to send individually which allowed them to personalize it just as customer success did the year before. The customer list needed to be reviewed and cleaned up and you stayed right on top of it! You shared feedback from the reps about how great their experience has been utilizing the email rather than handwriting cards that people throw away. This is a gift that keeps on giving! Thank you for truly owning this and working so hard to make sure it went off without a hitch!\n\n362#Bite-sized marketing updates, Buffet-sized results|Great job all on your collective sharings and updates during our full marketing team meeting this week. There is so much goodness happening in marketing right now and each of you showcased the strategic thinking, approach, and results in a very concise way. And...you also stayed on time! This shows how each of you respect each other and the full marketing team. It also ensured that everyone had an opportunity to share their work and create greater alignment across the entire group.  Thank you!\n\n363#28 this quarter!|28 humans. That's how many people assisted in one way or another with the Q4 year-end, last meeting of the decade and for each and every one of you, I am grateful! It's pretty incredible to think about the village that comes together to make this meeting happen. From confirming our speakers, creating slides, providing content, answering my many questions, testing and testing and testing (yes, 3x) the technology to provide a great experience for all, to ringing the gong - each of you receiving this award was integral to the overall success of the meeting.\n\n364#Tech champions support|I am deeply grateful for the support I received from each of you in preparation for speaking at Dublin Tech talks Meetup recently. From help with slides, distilling the many topics in my head down to something digestible, to help with my LinkedIn profile..You made a huge difference. Thank you\n\n365#You did it!|Earlier this week, our speaking proposal was accepted for the 2020 Recognition Professionals International (RPI) Conference. While that might seem like a no brainer to some, for years, the style and message of the conference didn't fit our brand, so years ago we stopped going. Chris & Corinne, you both kept it on your radar, and listened when future customers talked about it, and pitched reasons for us to relook at going. You both committed to do field research, and came back with feedback that not only should we have a presence there, but we should be speaking. Amy, you openly took in their feedback and experience and pursued it, put the the presentation proposal together with Corinne committing to speak and here we are, Success! Each of you maintained an open mindset for change and went the distance to make it happen, Congratulations!\n\n366#The value of leadership|Amy, while selecting the value for this award, I was wishing there was one specifically around leadership, because that‚Äôs the one you deserve. I‚Äôve been waiting to write this recognition for some time because it‚Äôs been clear in the months after your return just how impactful, insightful, and inspirational you are as a leader, colleague, and friend. You approach every project with a strategic lens, logic, calmness, and humor. You intrinsically see where people‚Äôs strengths are, what value they can add, and you empower them to do it with a mix of resolve, positivity, and kindness that‚Äôs truly motivating. To say I‚Äôve enjoyed working with you and benefitting from your guidance would be a gross understatement. You are, in a word, a powerhouse. And this place is so lucky to have you as one of its leaders. Thank you for all you do.\n\n367#For some amazing hand holding, prep and more!!!|Amy, you are an amazing partner in all of our outreach and I certainly have leaned on you these past weeks.  You have all the details to hand and are always a consummate professional.  I am extremely grateful that you are part of our team!  Thank you!\n\n368#2020 Digital Prep|Amy - Thank you for taking the time to meet with me to discuss the Digital/SEO/External Comms strategy in 2020. It was a great conversation, and it gave us both action items to accomplish goals both in the short term and deeper into the new year.  With what we were able to in just a few short months in 2019, I know we'll be able to raise Workhuman's web presence even more so in 2020.\n\n369#For a LinkedIn 101 1 on 1!|Hey guys. Thank you so much for the work with me on the thought leadership platform. It has made a tremendous difference and it is so reassuring to have experts like you both as supports as I navigate Social Media 101 material\n\n370#For lending an ear|Amy, thanks for taking the time to touch base