ran out of fingers, toes, and strands of hair to count on.  We basically crammed week‚Äôs worth of work into just two days, like it was nothing.  But it was everything!  This was no small feat, and every one of you played a role in pulling it off (almost) seamlessly.  The results are not in (yet), but this could not wait because we have completely set ourselves up for success thanks to all of you.  I so appreciate your focused commitment to the success of Workhuman Live.\n\n374#Interview Prep|Thank you so much for the interview prep sheet for our Irish Times interview this morning. It was so great to have all the numbers, customers and announcements to hand for quick reference! Of course, in the actual interview it veered into all manor of topics, but having the brief enabled me to quickly get us back on track! Well done and Thank You!\n\n375#Thanks to the data nerds|Thank you to everyone on this award for taking time to review questions and provide input for the upcoming full-time U.S. employee survey. What started out as a \"mini\" survey outside of the annual international survey has turned into quite a robust assessment of the employee experience in the U.S. We're tackling some sensitive issues such as harassment and discrimination and I really appreciate the thought each of you put into additional questions and answer options and getting the wording just right. I'm looking forward to seeing the results come in and using this data to build a compelling report that will drive leads and media inquires.\n\n376#Great experience!|Just wanted to thank you all for taking time out of your busy schedules to arrange time for me to get to observe and experience what you guys do on a daily basis. I was only in the Framingham office for a short period of time but I feel like I've obtained and learned a lot which is so beneficial to me. Your knowledge, talent and overall dedication to your work is extremely evident, thank you for the experience\n\n377#Team creativity|Thank you for your help collecting and sharing insightful, relevant information for our Q4 customer acceleration meetings.  With your contributions, we were able to identify marketing opportunities and generate new ideas for delivering value to these important accounts.  Looking forward to continued collaboration and the wealth of innovative ideas that will result!\n\n378#Finance work|Amy, thank you for all the creativity and passion you are bringing to helping us pursue the finance persona.  Whether it is the executive finance event, team briefings or market testing of messaging, you are at the forefront leading the charge. This is a new area for us and requires the courage to try new things, be bold and basically operate completely out of our comfort zone at all times.  But that is the kind of effort required to change the world.  We have to always do things that have not been done. And we have to take risks.  I wouldn't say endure failure but rather learn from all our experiments.  Bravo for stepping up to take on this challenge and for helping us learn a new approach.  So far so good!\n\n379#NewCo Lighthouse|Thank you for giving me and Christina the opportunity to run with the NewCo event and playing a role in building up our relationship with Mass TLC. Through planning this event we‚Äôve been able to build and strengthen relationships with different departments, while getting to experience how to be more successful with these types of events in the future. Your guidance on execution and recommendations of who and what to tap into helped to give us the confidence we needed to pull everything off! Thanks for your strong leadership, your confidence, and your support!\n\n380#GPTW Ire|Maeve and Amy, Thank you both for your help getting me the information on our top media pieces in Ireland and all of the great speaking engagements we've had this year. This information is going to be a great addition to our interactive submission this year, showing how we've raised our profile in the market! Thank you so much for your quick and thorough help.\n\n381#Campaign and Testing Progress!|Incredible job with your recent presentation on our campaigns.  Amy ‚Äì as the quarterback you have displayed great agility, fine-tuning and advances our approaches, new test ideas, and more. We are in the midst of a transformation within marketing ‚Äì from both a conceptional and executional standpoint. You were able to show the progress made to date, share key learnings, and demonstrate new opportunities in a very articulate way.  Katie ‚Äì you added tremendous value on the social media side and have already made an impact to the campaigns ‚Äì to ensure we are mindful of new testing methodologies as well as visual approaches that should increase our impact.  Thank you both for your great efforts!\n\n382#Adjustments on the fly|Team, It was only four business days ago that we sat down and talked about our experiences from the first few executive forums and re-envisioned what it could be. In the ensuing days, I know that you all worked tirelessly to create the new experience that we had in mind. Today‚Äôs session was amazing and light years ahead of where we were this time last week. It‚Äôs because you had the courage and energy to take those ideas and make them real earlier this week. Thank you, and well done!\n\n383#Bringing it all together|I started over a month ago and after getting very behind on my inbox, I wasn't exactly looking forward to another onboarding session. However, I truly enjoyed your presentation and really appreciated hearing hopes and visions for the future of Workhuman after mostly retrospectives and demonstrations. Not only did you call out and encourage participation and feedback from the group, but you were the only presenter (if memory serves) to describe how your role and department interacts with every one of us. In my mind, that's what onboarding should be. I look forward to working with you. Thanks!\n\n384#The happiest and most helpful humans of all.|Z and Amy, I cannot tell you how much I appreciate your help on some recent projects. Regardless of your workloads, regardless of how fragmented the asks, you are ALWAYS in my corner to help me navigate through all the things, help pick up the pieces and push on to a glorious and thoughtful end result. Thank you both for the awesome-ness, thoughtfulness and being AMAZING partners in crime. I don't know what I would do without you!\n\n385#agile tour presentation - Supporters!|Maeve, Amy and Jessica, thanks for all your support with my preparations for my presentation at the Agile Tour Dublin.  From the initial group training set up where the idea of presenting came about, to the individual training your arranged for me, the help with preparing the presentation and the on-the-day support with the Workhuman desk and raffle organisation; it all helped make this a success.  All this investment and preparation really worked and I received great feedback on the presentation at the event. I was really glad to have taken part in this new initiative and I look forward to my next presentation (or to attending one of your presentations! )\n\n386#Moments that matter in presenting!|Amy, thank you for offering your speaking engagement coaching expertise in preparation for the HR Tech presentation(s). I so appreciate your advice and honesty in how I can personally enhance my presentation style and approach. I took your feedback to heart and most definitely applied it during the real thing! Gratitudes, Amy!\n\n387#Bringing the Humanity at HR Tech|Dan, Amy, Mike, and Max - Wonderful work at the HR Tech conference in Las Vegas. Shows like this are an incredible opportunity to influence the market - through key influencers, analysts, customers, and more.  There are countless items that play into the strategy - from social presence to meetings to sessions to dinners to drinks to content. It's a constant flurry of activities that show who we are as a company and people. Thank you for the passion you brought, the eagerness to learn and make new connections, and all the great relationship building along the way!\n\n388#It takes a village.|I'd like to express my gratitude to this group of Workhuman superstars. Each of you stepped up in the last few weeks to contribute a post on the Workhuman blog. None of you are full-time writers, but each of you helped bring new stories and perspectives to our readers this month. From event recaps to personal gratitude stories to showing the business value of investing in recognition, these posts add to the rich fabric of thought leadership content our readers expect. Thank you for patiently working with me on rounds of edits and providing all those extra details like headshots, bios, and other images. Looking forward to more posts from you in the future!\n\n389#Off to a great start|Amy - this was a bit overdue, but now I have more to add! Thank you for being so open minded and enthusiastic about our new job kickoff process. Our meeting was the first time I had put this new process into play, and it was so energizing to have it so well-received by you. Not only were you willing to do a deep dive into all the things, but you came to our meeting SO well prepared - to discuss so many different aspects of your open position, your vision for PR, and the recruiting process. Since then, you've also taken the time to review resumes with me, and have stuck to your commitment to SUPER quick turnaround on candidate feedback. Thank you for such a great recruiting partner. I am truly looking forward to filling this job with you!\n\n390#Championing our Tech Community Champions|Ladies  ... I love the energy and passion you've both brought to this initiative!!  You've really led from the front, encouraging ideas and input and being super supportive to all. It's great to see the structure, supports, the encouragement and showcasing each individuals contribution and journey. Really well done, excited to see how this progresses .... super excited about our SWERVE lightening showcase!!\n\n391#It Takes an Army|I want to extend a special thank you to everyone involved in bringing together the Taste of Workhuman Live event series. Amanda/Amy for pulling together graticards, gratitude journals, speakers, coordinating content, setting up briefing meetings, and keeping everyone on track. Jess/Jen/Mike for the execution of campaign materials numerous operations requests, and fast turn-around timelines. Lynette - for being the rockstar that I knew you would be speaking at our events. Thanks for your constant energy and passion you bring to everything that you do. Also, for helping set up at Raleigh and Atlanta. Mark - for stepping up, helping research and cover for me while I was on vacation. Mike - for coming in last minute and saving the day with Laurie Ruettiman to speak at our events. Everyone made these events successful and spectacular. Thank you all!\n\n392#Exec Forum Powerhouse Partner|Amy - It was great to start off the Exec Forum fall tour with you by my side. You've been a powerhouse behind the scenes in securing executive speakers, managing changes on the fly, and helping to develop the messaging and content for the events. And your attitude and effort was no different on the ground - helping to set up, prep our speakers, welcome guests, have lively conversations, move tables, and take copious notes all along the way to capture the dialogue, discussion, and insights taking place in the room. I appreciate all that you bring to the table - and the forums - and I look forward to the future growth of the program with you on the team!\n\n393#The Workhuman Social Media Era Is Here|Amy, I wanted to say how much I appreciate how you have led Max and I these past few months. The social media team forming together is such a great opportunity for Workhuman and in some ways we were building it from the ground up. Lots of actions were already in place, but developing a whole new team is no easy feat! You always made it clear that you were available by any means. You helped guide us through all of these changes. You were able to provide your level of expertise to what we were doing to help us learn from you. You provided us support when we needed it. You are our #1 cheerleader. We have a lot of work ahead of us, but we are in a much better spot with your guidance and support. Excited to continue to partner and work with our new teams together! Thank you so much!\n\n394#MetroWest Women's Conference|I want to take a moment and thank you all for attending yesterday's event for the MetroWest Women's Conference. It was an successful event because we had some great leadership representing Workhuman as there lead Sponsor! Sarah, you were a true rockstar on stage! The recruiting team killed it at the table when people came running to see what jobs we had open after Sarah's keynote during breakfast! Kevin, Amy, Julia, and Miguel thank you for taking time out of your busy schedules to represent Workhuman! It was a great day and I can't wait to partner with MetroWest again next year!\n\n395#aaaaand feedback on the fly!|Amy, thank you so much for giving me some super valuable feedback on the fly after my presentation at the conference yesterday!  I truly value your input and I am so looking forward to more opportunities for critiquing in the future! and.. and..and...and....... Luda out!\n\n396#For Immediate Release: Amy Rice is a PR Superstar|Amy, working with you for the last month or so on Workhuman's PR and external comms efforts as well as competitor research has been so great. Thank you so much for seeking me out and getting me involved where you saw/see fit. We have a great process for how we handle our releases and articles and that's only going to continue to get better.   Also, thank you for being an advocate for me and my work. I have a tendency to dive into the deep end on projects, and you let me figure things out then suggest areas to look into that I might not have thought about. You also are more than accommodating when I have a question or a finding. It seems like you might have like 15 minutes a day when you're not in meetings so I really appreciate you taking a couple minutes to listen to things that I found.    I'm really looking forward to our continued partnership, and I think you and I can accomplish a lot of awesome things for Workhuman with our joint efforts.\n\n397#Two four six eight who do we appreciate!|Only fitting that during the first week of the football season we recognize our very own QB1.    Thank you for your hard work and determination in proving out this new process.  It‚Äôs a grind.  Sometimes it‚Äôs just three yards and a cloud of dust.  (Not sure what that has to do with it but I‚Äôm sticking with the football theme) It‚Äôs not always flashy but you make it work.  So pull back and launch that Hail Mary because we are about to win this game!  It is a joy to be have you leading the team!\n\n398#For a fantastic Tech Communication Training|Thank you, Amy and Maeve for setting up and running the technology communication training. This was a very high quality session and is an important part of building out our employer brand in the Irish Market. Thank you for putting so much work into making the session meaningful. I got a lot from it and I know from being in the room that the attendees did.\n\n399#Paving the Path for Program Success|Amy - It‚Äôs seems quite unbelievable that you‚Äôve only been back now a couple of months. In that time, you‚Äôve tackled a lot. A whole lot!  PR, campaigns, social, a new thought leadership/speaker platform strategy, and more.  These are huge initiatives that involve many people across the company (and many details behind the scenes). And many of them are entirely new approaches for marketing. Each and every time, you jump right in with enthusiasm, focus, and passion to achieving success for the company (you‚Äôre also unafraid to try anything new).   A high growth company like ours takes that type of mindset and leader. Thank you for your continual strong efforts!\n\n400#Let's do this thing.|TEAM! Super inspired after our meeting yesterday. I love where this is going and am appreciative of all the hard work, thought, preparation and leadership in completely changing the way we are approaching this company-wide initiative. I'm excited to be involved and be a part of something so much bigger than just one project or one department. Way to innovate and lead the charge. Times are a changin' and I am HERE for it!! Well done! #gratitag\n\n401#In the trenches!|Amy and Lauren - I cant begin to express how much I have enjoyed working with you both on our various campaigns and programs this past month. You are both so talented and I love that we almost immediately were in sync. It‚Äôs been so refreshing working alongside each of you and I love that we have found a way to collaborate without stepping on each other‚Äôs toes. Amy, your ability to build a framework and program around abstract creative ideas is excellent. Lauren: your ability to craft messaging and tell stories is what brings colors and picture to life. We won‚Äôt get everything right, (eh, we‚Äôre human) but it‚Äôs great to know that we have each other‚Äôs back and will figure things out together. :)\n\n402#The Gratitude Effect|I am SO excited about where we are headed for our Gratitude Effect campaign. As a core team, we are learning what hasn‚Äôt worked and trying our new improved approach for this one. We are off to such a strong, strategic and efficient approach, I can‚Äôt wait to reveal it with the larger team tomorrow. In true test and learn fashion, let‚Äôs see if it works but even if it doesn‚Äôt, you were all so willing and open to trying, what more could I ask for? I‚Äôm so grateful for you!\n\n403#Partnering to push things forward|Thank you to this team for helping push things forward to secure a c-level speaker for the upcoming Evanta Summit. Kevin - 