ure - with hard work and focus leading to \"our water\" - an incredible experience that will empower and enrich our leaders. On the content side, Dan - incredible leadership. You support and lift your team when they need it most - and spearhead so many other initiatives, particularly the post-show content strategy. Lauren C - words cannot fully describe your enormous impact on the event in managing our speakers and tracks. So many details - you get it done with poise, class, and determination. Sarah - your efforts leading our blog strategy has resulted in another step up for our on-site thought leadership. The bar has risen again! Lauren B - your creative approach continually up-levels the words that our attendees see throughout. And at the event, you were a huge part of the blogging efforts. Aaron and Lynne - fantastic job blogging at the conference, finding the right insights to help our attendees take back key learnings to help their organizations grow. Jess - while you were not able to join us at the event, you were invaluable leading up supporting so many writing needs (and your editing skills rock too!). For internal comms, Colleen - fantastic work leading our strategy this year, helping our company \"feel\" the event better than ever. Kristen - your creativity & determination brought it to life internally, plus your support on social was huge! Clare - loved your timely updates and great ideas. Your idea to ask Kat for an internal video was genius! For external comms, Mike - masterful job with our influencer community once again. Their engagement was incredible! 20 interviews including some of our keynotes with Workhuman Radio (your baby). Just amazing! And Amy, while you couldn't be there, your impact on our PR coverage was huge with some fantastic pieces and more to come. Thank you to the best comms and content team the event world has ever seen. Grateful for all of you.\n\n411#Rescue!|See that picture - that's you, jumping out of the 'copter to \"save\" me. In the lead up to the big event there is a lot going on. You've been a great teammate, offering to help at every turn. I am so very appreciative of you taking on the briefing book and getting it in such great shape while I was focused on other things this week. Thank you for all the great work you did and for continuing to say \"what else can I do to help?\" You're awesome!\n\n412#The Great Communicators of Workhuman|I am grateful for your collective amazing work on the brand evolution in the past couple of weeks. Each of you stepped up in different, very important ways to ensure we announced it to the wider world (and internally) in an effective, meaningful way. There were twists, turns, changes - but you rolled with it and focused on the larger objective. And of course, as big projects tend to do, the time needed to get everything done crept into evening hours (and sometimes early morning hours given our global needs). And yet, you were all undaunted and got it the timing and the messaging right.  Well done team!\n\n413#Making a Big Impact Immediately|Amy -  I am so very grateful that you joined the team. I have been so impressed and amazed by your work since coming aboard just a few weeks ago. You started during an incredibly busy time (even by our standards!) and have never been fazed. Even as we announce our brand evolution, you stepped right in to help bring it to market very successfully in both the US and Ireland. You continually ask the right questions, probe on the right topics, and are curious about the right areas of opportunity.  We have incredible momentum ahead for the company and brand, and your experience and knowledge has already paid dividends.  Cheers to the bright future ahead!  Kevin\n\n"
